WEBVTT

00:30.764 --> 00:33.734
Boy, voice-over: MY MOTHER
NAMED ME AFTER MY FATHER.

00:33.767 --> 00:36.770
ANGUS--A COW'S NAME,

00:36.804 --> 00:40.774
WHICH DIDN'T HELP MATTERS
MUCH BECAUSE I WAS A BIG KID.

00:47.681 --> 00:50.551
MY MOTHER WAS IN LABOR
WITH ME FOR TWO DAYS,

00:50.584 --> 00:53.321
BUT IT WAS MY FATHER
WHO DIED DURING CHILDBIRTH.

00:53.354 --> 00:55.323
HE HAD A HEART ATTACK
WAITING FOR HER TO DELIVER.

00:55.356 --> 00:57.258
BUT THIS WASN'T
REALLY MY PROBLEM.

00:57.291 --> 01:01.262
IN FACT, I PERCEIVED MY FAMILY
SITUATION AS RELATIVELY NORMAL,

01:01.295 --> 01:05.166
UNTIL I BEGAN COLLECTING
EXPERT FEEDBACK
AROUND KINDERGARTEN.

01:05.199 --> 01:08.336
ANGUS BETHUNE
IS A FAT KID.

01:08.369 --> 01:10.738
Boy: HE'S SO HUNGRY,
HE EATS HIS BOOGERS!

01:10.771 --> 01:12.173
[Kids laughing]

01:12.206 --> 01:14.175
Angus, voice-over:
THIS WAS MY PROBLEM:

01:14.208 --> 01:15.476
RICK SANFORD.

01:18.546 --> 01:22.316
HEY, ANGUS, WANNA
PLAY "PIN THE TAIL
ON THE DONKEY"?

01:22.350 --> 01:24.852
YOU CAN BE THE DONKEY.

01:24.885 --> 01:28.456
WHOA!

01:28.489 --> 01:32.160
WHOA! YOU BROKE
HIS NOSE, ANGUS!

01:32.193 --> 01:35.596
YOU WANNA SEE IT?
FIVE CENTS.

01:35.629 --> 01:37.598
Angus, voice-over:
I MET MY BEST FRIEND,
TROY WEDBERG,

01:37.631 --> 01:39.567
THE DAY HE CHARGED
FIVE CENTS TO SEE--

01:39.600 --> 01:42.136
MY COUSIN'S PUBIC HAIR!

01:42.170 --> 01:43.904
WHOA!
WHOA!

01:43.937 --> 01:47.441
[STALL DOOR OPENS]
UH-OH.

01:47.475 --> 01:50.844
AHEM. NO WAY.

01:50.878 --> 01:53.447
YOU ARE SUCH A LIAR.

01:53.481 --> 01:56.617
GIVE HIM HIS PUBIC HAIR
BACK, RICK.

01:56.650 --> 01:59.687
ANGUS.
ISN'T ANGUS A COW?

01:59.720 --> 02:01.555
[KIDS GIGGLING]

02:03.257 --> 02:04.558
OW!

02:04.592 --> 02:06.560
MOO.

02:06.594 --> 02:08.262
Boy: YOU BROKE HIS NOSE, ANGUS!

02:08.295 --> 02:10.231
Angus, voice-over:
I WAS INCREDIBLY
QUICK FOR A FAT KID

02:10.264 --> 02:12.566
AND GRADES CAME
PRETTY EASY TO ME.
THANKS!

02:12.600 --> 02:15.603
BUT I WAS SURE WILLING
TO SWAP IT ALL FOR
A LITTLE PHYSICAL BEAUTY.

02:15.636 --> 02:20.174
[OVER P.A.]
* IF I DIDN'T LOVE YOU,
I'D HATE YOU... *

02:20.208 --> 02:23.577
Girl: TAKE IT BACK!
I DON'T HAVE HAIRY LEGS!

02:23.611 --> 02:24.778
COME ON! LET GO!

02:24.812 --> 02:26.847
I FELL IN LOVE
WITH MELISSA LEFEVRE...

02:26.880 --> 02:29.883
THE DAY SHE THREW
ALEX IMMERGLUCH
ACROSS TARLO'S ROLLER RINK.

02:29.917 --> 02:32.853
WHOA!
[CRASH]

02:32.886 --> 02:34.588
MELISSA LEFEVRE WAS
THAT GIRL

02:34.622 --> 02:36.424
THAT JUST MADE YOU ACHE...

02:36.457 --> 02:38.359
BECAUSE YOU KNOW
SHE WAS PUT ON THIS EARTH
OUT OF YOUR REACH

02:38.392 --> 02:39.860
ONLY TO MAKE YOU FEEL BAD.

02:39.893 --> 02:42.796
ANGUS. ANGUS!

02:42.830 --> 02:43.764
ANGUS!

02:47.835 --> 02:50.671
Angus, voice-over:
RICK SANFORD GOT
MORE POPULAR.

02:50.704 --> 02:52.406
WANNA PLAY
SOME FOOTBALL?

02:52.440 --> 02:54.308
YEAH, SURE.

02:54.342 --> 02:56.444
GOOD. YOU CAN BE THE FIELD.

02:56.477 --> 02:57.678
[LAUGHTER]

02:57.711 --> 03:00.248
HA HA.

03:00.281 --> 03:02.683
AND MUCH BETTER LOOKING
EVERY TIME I BROKE HIS NOSE.

03:02.716 --> 03:04.918
YOU BROKE
HIS NOSE, ANGUS.

03:04.952 --> 03:06.887
Rick: OW!

03:06.920 --> 03:08.322
WHAT'S MELISSA DOING?

03:08.356 --> 03:09.990
Melissa:
RICK, ARE YOU OK?

03:10.023 --> 03:12.293
Angus, voice-over:
WORSE, HE GOT
MELISSA LEFEVRE.

03:12.326 --> 03:14.962
SHE'S MAKING
SURE RICK'S OK.

03:14.995 --> 03:17.465
[DRUMS BEATING]

03:17.498 --> 03:18.799
WHAT'S MELISSA DOING?

03:18.832 --> 03:21.235
SHE'S TRYING TO SEE
IF RICK'S OK.

03:21.269 --> 03:22.236
ARE YOU OK?

03:22.270 --> 03:23.271
YEAH. I'M FINE.

03:23.304 --> 03:25.639
[INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENTS]

03:30.978 --> 03:33.747
I HATE THAT GUY.

03:33.781 --> 03:34.948
A LITTLE BIT...

03:34.982 --> 03:36.584
Angus, voice-over:
GOLDEN RICK SANFORD.

03:36.617 --> 03:41.322
HE HAD EVERYTHING--
LOOKS, SMARTS, AND MELISSA.

03:41.355 --> 03:44.325
I HAD TROY, AND HE HAD--

03:44.358 --> 03:45.993
[WHISPERING]
JOCK ITCH.

03:46.026 --> 03:48.829
LET'S GO!
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

03:48.862 --> 03:50.698
[CROWD CHEERING]

04:03.010 --> 04:05.679
* THERE'S TOO MUCH

04:05.713 --> 04:07.981
* THAT I KEEP

04:08.015 --> 04:10.351
* TO MYSELF

04:10.384 --> 04:14.955
* AND I TURN MY BACK
ON MY FAITH *

04:14.988 --> 04:17.358
* IT'S LIKE GLASS

04:17.391 --> 04:24.532
* WHEN WE BREAK,
I WISH NO ONE IN MY PLACE *

04:24.565 --> 04:26.400
* AND I'VE SEEN

04:26.434 --> 04:30.804
* YOU DON'T NEED THEIR SEEDS

04:30.838 --> 04:35.376
* WHEN THEIR CUT GOES IN DEEP

04:35.409 --> 04:40.381
* AND I'M LOST IN SLEEP

04:40.414 --> 04:44.718
* I CAN'T STAY
IN THIS PLACE *

04:44.752 --> 04:51.659
* I CAN'T STAND WHEN THE ROOM
TURNS 'ROUND ON MY FATE *

04:51.692 --> 04:53.927
* YOU GIVE NO

04:53.961 --> 04:56.029
* GUARANTEES

04:56.063 --> 05:00.901
* THERE'S NO PROMISE
I CAN KEEP *

05:00.934 --> 05:02.903
* I CAN'T STARE

05:02.936 --> 05:07.408
* I CAN'T SEE MY WAY

05:07.441 --> 05:12.413
* I FEEL BLIND ON MY FEET

05:12.446 --> 05:16.817
* I CAN'T STAY TOO LONG

05:16.850 --> 05:19.319
* AM I WRONG?

05:27.628 --> 05:31.999
* GOOD-BYE,
LAY THE BLAME ON LUCK *

05:32.032 --> 05:36.804
* GOOD-BYE
LAY THE BLAME ON LUCK *

05:36.837 --> 05:41.074
* GOOD-BYE
LAY THE BLAME ON LUCK *

05:41.108 --> 05:46.814
* GOOD-BYE
LAY THE BLAME ON LUCK *

05:46.847 --> 05:48.682
[CROWD CHEERING]

05:54.988 --> 05:59.760
* GOOD-BYE,
LAY THE BLAME ON LUCK *

05:59.793 --> 06:04.164
* GOOD-BYE,
LAY THE BLAME ON LUCK *

06:04.197 --> 06:08.836
* GOOD-BYE,
LAY THE BLAME ON LUCK *

06:08.869 --> 06:15.876
* GOOD-BYE
LAY THE BLAME ON LUCK... *

06:17.845 --> 06:19.480
BE CAREFUL.

06:19.513 --> 06:21.615
[P.A. ANNOUNCEMENTS]

06:28.856 --> 06:30.491
Angus, voice-over: GROWING UP,

06:30.524 --> 06:32.660
YOU WAIT FOR THAT ONE MOMENT
THAT'S TRULY YOURS...

06:32.693 --> 06:35.496
FOR SOMETHING TO HAPPEN
THAT MAKES YOU BELIEVE,
MAYBE ONCE IN A WHILE,

06:35.529 --> 06:37.631
THE GOOD GUYS CAN WIN.

06:37.665 --> 06:39.099
I WAS STILL WAITING.

06:40.668 --> 06:42.035
Cheerleaders:
GO! FIGHT...

06:42.069 --> 06:44.505
COME ON, HUSKIES.
LET'S...

06:44.538 --> 06:46.607
Rick: RUN THE PLAY AGAIN.

06:46.640 --> 06:48.842
MIKE, YOU GOT TO MAKE
SURE YOU WAIT TILL
THE LANE CLEARS OUT...

06:48.876 --> 06:51.512
BEFORE YOU CUT,
ALL RIGHT? OR ELSE I GOT
NOTHING TO THROW TO.

06:51.545 --> 06:52.846
ALL RIGHT.
YOU KNOW WHAT IT IS.

06:52.880 --> 06:56.183
SPLIT BACK RIGHT. FLAG
POST, FLAG ON ONE. READY?

06:56.216 --> 06:57.885
BREAK!
BREAK!

06:57.918 --> 06:59.019
WATCH MY ASS.

06:59.052 --> 07:00.988
I'M WATCHING IT
RIGHT NOW.

07:01.021 --> 07:02.623
I BET YOU ARE.

07:08.529 --> 07:09.730
[HORN BLOWS]

07:09.763 --> 07:11.632
Angus, voice-over:
IT WAS NEARLY IMPOSSIBLE

07:11.665 --> 07:13.166
FOR A DEFENSIVE LINEMAN
TO SHAKE ME.

07:13.200 --> 07:16.870
I WAS A WALL.

07:16.904 --> 07:20.541
Rick: RED, 34. RED, 34.

07:20.574 --> 07:21.709
SET! HUT!

07:28.816 --> 07:32.586
Boy: PASS! HE'S GOING LONG!

07:37.925 --> 07:40.193
I GOT IT! AH!

07:40.227 --> 07:41.995
OHH!

07:43.931 --> 07:45.499
DAMN!
I'LL TAKE HIM!

07:45.533 --> 07:47.167
Angus, voice-over:
IN ADDITION, I WAS EQUIPPED

07:47.200 --> 07:48.936
WITH TRACKING RADAR.

07:48.969 --> 07:50.804
I NEEDED ONLY TO LOCK IN
ON A CORNERBACK'S HIPS

07:50.838 --> 07:52.540
TO ZERO IN ON THE TACKLE.

08:08.556 --> 08:11.224
I, ANGUS BETHUNE,
HAD CAUSED A FUMBLE.

08:11.258 --> 08:15.996
THE BALL--MY BALL--
SOARED THROUGH THE AIR,
FREE LIKE AN EAGLE,

08:16.029 --> 08:20.200
AND THEN...IT LANDED
IN RICK SANFORD'S HANDS.

08:20.233 --> 08:22.970
GO! GO, RICK! GO!

08:23.003 --> 08:25.005
GO, GO, GO, RICK! GO!

08:25.038 --> 08:31.879
[CROWD CHANTING,
"GO, RICK! GO!"]

08:31.912 --> 08:32.980
[MOANS]

08:39.052 --> 08:40.320
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

08:40.352 --> 08:42.022
[OVER P.A.]
TOUCHDOWN, HUSKIES!

08:42.054 --> 08:43.624
YEAH!

08:43.657 --> 08:44.658
Angus, voice-over:
I HAD CAUSED THE FUMBLE

08:44.692 --> 08:46.660
THAT WON US THE GAME.

08:46.694 --> 08:48.996
I WAS SURE, ANY MINUTE NOW,
THEY WOULD COME RUNNING
TOWARD ME, CHEERING,

08:49.029 --> 08:51.198
"ANGUS! ANGUS!"

08:51.231 --> 08:53.266
Students:
RICK! RICK! RICK!

08:53.300 --> 08:54.935
RICK! RICK!
RICK! RICK!

08:54.968 --> 08:57.705
GREAT JOB, RICK!

08:57.738 --> 09:00.674
RICK! RICK! RICK!

09:00.708 --> 09:01.975
OHH.

09:02.009 --> 09:04.645
YEAH!

09:04.678 --> 09:05.646
ALL RIGHT!

09:05.679 --> 09:06.980
NICE!

09:07.014 --> 09:09.149
Coach: YOU GUYS, I TOLD
YOU YOU COULD DO IT.

09:09.182 --> 09:12.853
Angus, voice-over: SO THERE
HE WAS, WITH MY VICTORY.

09:12.886 --> 09:16.289
AND JUST ONCE I WANTED
TO KNOW WHAT IT WOULD FEEL
LIKE TO BE LIKE HIM--

09:16.323 --> 09:19.760
ON TOP OF THE WORLD,
JUST FOR ONE MOMENT.

09:19.793 --> 09:21.261
* WOULD YOU TALK TO ME

09:23.196 --> 09:24.798
* HONESTLY?

09:26.333 --> 09:29.703
* 'CAUSE I NEVER HEARD
A WORD YOU SAID, NOW *

09:29.737 --> 09:33.006
* AND I AIN'T JUST BEIN' MEAN

09:33.040 --> 09:36.309
* 'CAUSE ALL WE ARE
IS WHAT WE'RE TOLD *

09:36.343 --> 09:39.680
* AND MOST OF THAT'S
BEEN LIES *

09:39.713 --> 09:43.050
* IT'S LIKE
A MADE-FOR-TV MOVIE *

09:43.083 --> 09:46.186
* AND I JUST BLEW
MY LINE... *

09:46.219 --> 09:50.023
I'M TRYING TO PROVE
THAT IF YOU PUT A SMALL,
ABNORMAL ELEMENT...

09:50.057 --> 09:52.359
IN A LARGE,
HOMOGENEOUS SYSTEM,

09:52.392 --> 09:55.963
THE SYSTEM WILL REJECT
THE DEVIATION...

09:55.996 --> 09:57.698
RATHER THAN MUTATE,

09:57.731 --> 10:01.702
USUALLY CAUSING A POWERFUL
EXOTHERMIC REACTION.

10:05.773 --> 10:07.841
OOH!
[BELL RINGING]

10:10.077 --> 10:11.044
Teacher:
EXCELLENT, ANGUS.

10:11.078 --> 10:12.980
Boy: FINALLY.

10:20.387 --> 10:21.955
THANK YOU.

10:21.989 --> 10:23.056
SEE YOU
AFTER PRACTICE.

10:23.090 --> 10:24.324
Rick: YEAH, SEE YOU LATER.

10:28.361 --> 10:29.730
WOW.
GOOD POOF, ANGUS.

10:29.763 --> 10:31.064
HA HA!

10:31.098 --> 10:32.432
Short boy:
GREAT WORK, EINSTEIN.

10:32.465 --> 10:35.736
Teacher: RICK, GREAT
TOUCHDOWN YESTERDAY.

10:35.769 --> 10:37.738
THANKS.

10:37.771 --> 10:40.373
DID YOU SEE
MY BLOCK?
YES.

10:40.407 --> 10:41.875
YOU SCORED.

10:44.111 --> 10:48.015
ANGUS, THE PRINCIPAL
WANTS TO SEE YOU.

10:56.724 --> 10:57.891
[SNIFFING]

11:01.328 --> 11:04.297
[YAWNS]

11:10.303 --> 11:12.005
WELL...

11:12.039 --> 11:14.775
YOUR APPLICATION
TO JEFFERSON...

11:14.808 --> 11:18.078
HAS BEEN ACCEPTED,
ANGUS.

11:18.111 --> 11:21.414
JEFFERSON IS
THE BEST MAGNET SCHOOL
IN THE DISTRICT.

11:21.448 --> 11:23.851
YOU'LL HAVE TO DO
A SCIENCE PROJECT.

11:23.884 --> 11:26.920
IT'S ALL IN THE LETTER.

11:26.954 --> 11:30.023
IT'S A WONDERFUL
OPPORTUNITY, ANGUS.

11:32.826 --> 11:35.796
OF COURSE,
IF YOU DON'T GO,

11:35.829 --> 11:39.232
I WON'T HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT
LOSING OUR BEST J.V. TACKLE.

11:39.266 --> 11:42.135
ANGUS?

11:42.169 --> 11:43.771
THANK YOU, SIR.

11:48.075 --> 11:50.110
[GROANING]

11:50.143 --> 11:52.045
Angus, voice-over:
MY MOM THINKS I'M PERFECT.

11:52.079 --> 11:54.314
BUT THAT'S COMING FROM
SOMEONE WHO DRIVES A TRUCK...

11:54.347 --> 11:57.918
AND WHOSE CB HANDLE
IS "BRUISER."

11:57.951 --> 12:01.488
DON'T OVERREACT,
BUT I GOT MY INTERVIEW
FOR JEFFERSON.

12:01.521 --> 12:03.123
YOU'RE IN!

12:03.156 --> 12:04.391
JUST AN INTERVIEW.

12:04.424 --> 12:05.993
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME!

12:06.026 --> 12:07.327
I'M TELLING YOU.
OH, YOU'RE IN!

12:07.360 --> 12:08.328
YOU'RE OVERREACTING.

12:08.361 --> 12:10.163
I'M GONNA TELL
MY FATHER!

12:10.197 --> 12:11.765
I CAN'T BREATHE!

12:11.799 --> 12:15.168
I DON'T OVERREACT.
MOM.

12:15.202 --> 12:17.537
HEY, I GET IT, OK?
IT'S JUST AN INTERVIEW.

12:17.570 --> 12:19.372
YOU MIGHT NOT GET IN.
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

12:19.406 --> 12:22.342
YOU GET IN, YOU DON'T
GET IN. YOU THINK I CARE?

12:22.375 --> 12:23.844
[BELL DINGS]

12:23.877 --> 12:25.745
GO CALL YOUR GRANDFATHER.
TIME FOR DINNER.

12:31.051 --> 12:34.187
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

12:34.221 --> 12:36.189
Angus, voice-over:
MY GRANDFATHER--

12:36.223 --> 12:38.191
HE WAS AS SMART
AS THEY COME...

12:38.225 --> 12:39.893
WHEN HE WAS AWAKE.

12:52.405 --> 12:54.374
[NEEDLE DROPS ON RECORD]

12:54.407 --> 12:56.143
[TRUMPET PLAYING "REVEILLE"]

12:56.176 --> 12:58.411
I'M AWAKE, DAMN IT!
AHEM!

13:10.924 --> 13:12.092
[CHUCKLES]

13:15.095 --> 13:16.396
POTATOES.

13:25.272 --> 13:26.907
EASY ON THE SALT, DAD.

13:26.940 --> 13:28.608
MM-HMM.

13:28.641 --> 13:32.412
YOU KNOW, ANGUS GOT
HIS INTERVIEW FOR JEFFERSON.

13:32.445 --> 13:34.514
YOU KNOW,
AUNT RUTHIE R.S.V.P.'d.

13:34.547 --> 13:36.583
Mom: OH, THAT REMINDS ME.

13:36.616 --> 13:39.419
I TALKED TO THE CATERERS,
AND I THINK
THE BEST WAY TO GO...

13:39.452 --> 13:43.256
IS TO HAVE
TWO BUFFET TABLES--
ONE HOT AND ONE COLD.

13:43.290 --> 13:45.625
YOU KNOW,
BARRY'S COMING TOO.

13:45.658 --> 13:48.428
UNCLE BARRY R.S.V.P.'d?

13:48.461 --> 13:50.063
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
HE R.S.V.P.'d!

13:50.097 --> 13:53.233
IS HE BRINGING WEDNESDAY
AND PUGSLEY?

13:53.266 --> 13:54.567
HE'S BRINGING
THE WHOLE CLAN.

13:54.601 --> 13:57.104
I GUESS THEY CAN STAY
IN ANGUS' ROOM.

13:57.137 --> 13:58.571
SHARE MY ROOM? GET REAL!

13:58.605 --> 14:00.540
NO. YOU'LL STAY
IN YOUR GRANDPA'S ROOM.

14:00.573 --> 14:03.110
I'M NOT SLEEPING
WITH HIM.

14:03.143 --> 14:06.146
HE SNORES,
BIG NOSE HAIR SNORES!

14:06.179 --> 14:08.215
HE GRINDS HIS TEETH
IN HIS SLEEP.

14:08.248 --> 14:10.550
Angus: AT LEAST
THESE ARE REALLY MY TEETH.

14:10.583 --> 14:11.985
THESE ARE MY TEETH.

14:12.019 --> 14:14.287
I GUESS.
YOU PAID FOR 'EM.

14:14.321 --> 14:18.926
Mom: YOU KNOW, DAD,
APRIL'S INSISTING
ON PICKING THE BAND.

14:18.959 --> 14:21.194
WELL, IT'S
HER WEDDING, TOO.

14:21.228 --> 14:22.562
IT'S A POLKA BAND.

14:22.595 --> 14:25.232
Angus: MOM, DON'T START.

14:25.265 --> 14:27.467
LOOK, THIS IS
HARD ENOUGH TO GET TOGETHER

14:27.500 --> 14:29.136
AT THE LAST MINUTE.

14:29.169 --> 14:31.304
WHY DO THEY HAVE TO
GET MARRIED ANYWAY?

14:31.338 --> 14:33.440
SHE'S 30 YEARS
YOUNGER THAN HIM.

14:33.473 --> 14:35.976
WHY DON'T THEY JUST
LIVE TOGETHER?

14:36.009 --> 14:37.344
WHY IS SHE
TALKING TO ME

14:37.377 --> 14:38.979
LIKE I'M NOT
IN THE ROOM?

14:39.012 --> 14:40.914
WHY IS SHE TALKING TO ME
LIKE I'M AN ADULT?

14:40.948 --> 14:42.682
WHO GETS MARRIED AT 72?

14:42.715 --> 14:44.985
I AM 71.

14:45.018 --> 14:47.620
Mom: IT'S NOT NORMAL.
SHE'S NOT NORMAL.

14:47.654 --> 14:49.422
THE WHOLE IDEA'S RIDICULOUS,

14:49.456 --> 14:50.657
BUT I'M JUST SUPPOSED
TO GO ALONG WITH EVERYTHING.

14:50.690 --> 14:52.459
MOM.

14:52.492 --> 14:54.261
WHAT?

14:54.294 --> 14:55.562
HE'S ASLEEP.

15:01.668 --> 15:03.336
DAD.

15:05.672 --> 15:08.008
IS SHE GONE?

15:08.041 --> 15:09.676
YEAH, SHE'S GONE.

15:11.411 --> 15:12.412
GRANDPA?

15:12.445 --> 15:16.349
HMM?
YOU'RE 73.

15:16.383 --> 15:18.618
[MUSIC PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK]

15:22.689 --> 15:26.359
* WE WERE WALKING IN,
WALKING IN TWO WORLDS *

15:26.393 --> 15:29.229
* IN THE GARDENS
OF SUNLIGHT, HOME... *

15:29.262 --> 15:31.198
[SNORTS]

15:31.231 --> 15:33.700
[INHALING]

15:33.733 --> 15:36.970
I'M SWALLOWING SNOT!

15:41.241 --> 15:44.111
YOU KNOW,
IT DOESN'T TASTE THAT GROSS.

15:49.716 --> 15:51.384
WHY DO I SWEAT SO MUCH?

15:51.418 --> 15:52.552
WHAT?!

15:52.585 --> 15:54.221
WHY DO I SWEAT SO MUCH?

15:54.254 --> 15:56.456
SHH! I WANNA HEAR
WHAT THEY'RE PLAYING.

15:56.489 --> 15:58.125
EVERY TIME THEY
PLAY GREEN DAY,

15:58.158 --> 16:00.227
THE FIRST CALLER
GETS FREE TICKETS
TO THEIR CONCERT!

16:00.260 --> 16:01.694
[GIRL LAUGHS]

16:01.728 --> 16:04.031
Boy: HEY, ANY ROOM OVER
HERE? MAYBE ON YOUR LAP?

16:04.064 --> 16:07.200
HI! I'M GREAT.
COME ON.

16:12.639 --> 16:14.241
WHAT HAVE YOU
BEEN TALKING ABOUT?

16:14.274 --> 16:15.642
UH...
GEOMETRY.

16:15.675 --> 16:17.510
[CONVERSATION CONTINUES,
INDISTINCT]

16:21.448 --> 16:24.617
YOU KNOW, IF YOU GO
TO JEFFERSON--NERD HIGH--

16:24.651 --> 16:26.286
YOU MIGHT AS WELL
BECOME A MONK.

16:26.319 --> 16:28.021
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

16:28.055 --> 16:30.123
YOU BECOME A SCIENCE GEEK.

16:30.157 --> 16:31.591
NO WAY YOU'RE
GONNA GET BABES.

16:31.624 --> 16:33.426
GIRLS DON'T WANT BRAINS.

16:33.460 --> 16:35.495
THEY WANT GUYS
WHO ARE DANGEROUS,

16:35.528 --> 16:38.365
HAVE TATTOOS,
PLAY THE GUITAR.

16:38.398 --> 16:40.667
STICK WITH ME.
I KNOW THESE THINGS.

16:40.700 --> 16:44.437
YOU PLAY THE ACCORDION.

16:44.471 --> 16:47.074
YOU CAN MAKE A LIVING
PLAYING THE ACCORDION.

16:47.107 --> 16:48.441
YOU'RE GOOD AT IT.

16:48.475 --> 16:50.610
YOU CAN MAKE A LIVING
EATING FOOD.

16:50.643 --> 16:52.112
YOU'RE GREAT AT IT.

16:52.145 --> 16:54.081
YOU'RE SHORT.
YOU'RE FAT.

16:54.114 --> 16:55.515
YOU'RE PATHETIC.

16:55.548 --> 16:59.119
YOU'RE...FAT!

16:59.152 --> 17:00.587
BUDS!
BUDS!

17:00.620 --> 17:02.289
DON'T FORGET TO VOTE
FOR THE WINTER BALL DANCE.

17:02.322 --> 17:03.690
DON'T FORGET TO VOTE.

17:03.723 --> 17:05.458
DON'T FORGET TO VOTE
FOR THE DANCE.

17:05.492 --> 17:07.627
DON'T FORGET TO VOTE.

17:07.660 --> 17:09.296
DON'T FORGET TO VOTE
FOR THE WINTER BALL DANCE.

17:09.329 --> 17:12.232
KING AND QUEEN.
REMEMBER, YOUR VOTE COUNTS.

17:15.768 --> 17:18.637
DON'T FORGET TO VOTE.
DON'T FORGET TO VOTE...

17:18.671 --> 17:20.807
OW! HUBBA-HUBBA.

17:20.839 --> 17:22.209
DON'T FORGET
TO VOTE.

17:25.678 --> 17:27.347
YOU KNOW
WHAT WOULD BE FUNNY?

17:27.380 --> 17:30.150
IF WE WENT
TO THE DANCE.

17:30.183 --> 17:31.784
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

17:31.818 --> 17:34.154
WATCH EVERYONE SPAZ OUT
ON THE DANCE FLOOR.

17:34.187 --> 17:35.555
LOOK AT ALL THE DILDOS
STANDING AROUND,

17:35.588 --> 17:37.157
PRETENDING TO WANT
TO BE THERE.

17:37.190 --> 17:40.160
TROY,
WE ARE THOSE DILDOS.

17:40.193 --> 17:43.163
IT'S JUST FOR KICKS.

17:43.196 --> 17:45.665
YOUR MOM'S MAKING YOU
GO TO THE DANCE.

17:45.698 --> 17:47.500
WHY DID YOU TELL HER
ABOUT IT?

17:47.534 --> 17:50.803
I DON'T TELL HER
EVERYTHING.

17:50.837 --> 17:52.339
GREEN DAY! PHONE!

17:52.372 --> 17:54.674
HEY!
SHIT.

17:54.707 --> 17:56.643
FAGGOT PINHEAD,
YOU BETTER WATCH IT.

17:58.478 --> 18:00.680
HEY, LAY OFF, MAN.

18:00.713 --> 18:03.783
THANKS FOR THE TACKLE,
BUFFOON--BETHUNE.

18:03.816 --> 18:06.986
IGNORE HIM, ANGUS.
HE'S AN ASSHOLE.

18:10.857 --> 18:11.824
ANGUS!

18:13.560 --> 18:15.195
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM HERE?

18:16.696 --> 18:18.531
YOU GOT A TEMPER?

18:18.565 --> 18:19.832
SAVE IT FOR
THE FOOTBALL FIELD.

18:19.866 --> 18:22.469
BUT HE--
SAVE IT, ANGUS.

18:22.502 --> 18:24.604
IF YOU WANT
OUT OF HERE,

18:24.637 --> 18:26.439
I CAN ARRANGE IT
RIGHT NOW.

18:26.473 --> 18:27.640
IF YOU WANT
INTO JEFFERSON,
YOU'RE

18:27.674 --> 18:29.376
GOING TO HAVE
TO DO BETTER
THAN THIS.

18:29.409 --> 18:31.578
ONE SUSPENSION,
YOU'LL LOSE
YOUR SHOT.

18:31.611 --> 18:33.380
AND I WILL
SUSPEND YOU,
ANGUS.

18:35.882 --> 18:37.384
[BELL RINGS]

18:37.417 --> 18:39.219
Principal: ALL RIGHT.
LET'S CLEAR OUT.

18:39.252 --> 18:42.189
COME ON. COME ON. NOTHING
TO LOOK AT. LET'S GO.

18:56.236 --> 18:59.272
WHAT'S WITH
THE SAD PUPPY LOOK?

18:59.306 --> 19:01.941
MELISSA MOVE AWAY
OR SOMETHING?

19:01.974 --> 19:04.244
TALK TO HER. HUH?

19:04.277 --> 19:07.347
JUST ONCE BEFORE I DIE.
WILL YOU DO THAT, PLEASE?

19:07.380 --> 19:09.882
GRANDPA,
SHE'S POPULAR.

19:09.916 --> 19:11.584
YOU'RE NOT?

19:11.618 --> 19:13.186
I'M A BABE MAGNET.

19:13.220 --> 19:14.521
[LAUGHS]

19:14.554 --> 19:16.389
IT RUNS IN THE FAMILY.

19:17.790 --> 19:20.827
GRANDPA,
EVERYONE WILL
THINK I'M A JERK.

19:20.860 --> 19:23.330
ANGUS, REMEMBER
THESE WORDS...

19:23.363 --> 19:26.199
AND ALWAYS LIVE BY THEM--

19:26.233 --> 19:28.901
"SCREW 'EM!" WHO
CARES WHAT ANYBODY THINKS?

19:28.935 --> 19:31.338
I DO.

19:31.371 --> 19:33.240
MOVE!

19:35.808 --> 19:39.279
YOU THINK I DON'T KNOW
HOW HARD IT IS TO TALK
TO A GIRL? I KNOW!

19:39.312 --> 19:42.482
WASN'T EASY FOR ME
TO ASK APRIL OUT.
YOU KNOW WHY I DID IT?

19:42.515 --> 19:44.484
'CAUSE YOU'RE
OLD AND SENILE?

19:44.517 --> 19:46.619
'CAUSE I SAID, "SCREW 'EM."

19:46.653 --> 19:48.221
ANY MINUTE NOW,
YOU'RE GONNA
START DROOLING.

19:48.255 --> 19:49.456
I WENT AHEAD AND ASKED HER.

19:49.489 --> 19:51.291
I'M NOT GOING TO BE
YOUR DROOL WIPER.

19:51.324 --> 19:52.792
I DIDN'T CARE
WHAT ANYBODY THOUGHT.

19:52.825 --> 19:55.462
YOU CAN'T REMEMBER
WHAT ANYBODY
THINKS ANYWAY.

19:55.495 --> 19:56.863
YOUR MIND IS SHOT.

20:00.667 --> 20:03.503
GRANDPA, YOU DON'T TALK
TO MELISSA LEFEVRE

20:03.536 --> 20:06.339
WHEN YOU'RE THE FAT KID
WHO'S GOOD AT SCIENCE.

20:06.373 --> 20:08.941
YOU'RE NOT THE FAT KID
WHO'S GOOD AT FOOTBALL?

20:08.975 --> 20:11.944
ANGUS, YOU'RE NOT FAT.

20:11.978 --> 20:14.314
YOU COME FROM BIG PEOPLE.
MY FATHER WAS BIG.

20:14.347 --> 20:16.816
YOUR GRANDMOTHER,
SHE WAS BIG.

20:16.849 --> 20:20.253
YOU'RE NORMAL
FOR WHERE YOU COME FROM.

20:20.287 --> 20:21.454
I'M NOT NORMAL.

20:21.488 --> 20:23.490
WELL, I'M BIG. I'M NORMAL.

20:23.523 --> 20:25.858
YOU'RE DEFINITELY
NOT NORMAL.

20:25.892 --> 20:28.795
YOU'RE AT AN IRRITATING AGE.

20:28.828 --> 20:30.463
SO ARE YOU.

20:34.367 --> 20:36.235
IT'S TIME
TO TAKE YOUR PILL.

20:43.876 --> 20:46.045
FINALLY!

20:46.078 --> 20:48.681
* KUNG FU,
DO WHAT YOU DO TO ME *

20:48.715 --> 20:52.385
* I HAVEN'T BEEN THE SAME
SINCE MY TEENAGE
LOBOTOMY... *

20:52.419 --> 20:54.521
THEY SENT OUT
SCHOOL SPIRIT
DAY FLIERS.

20:54.554 --> 20:56.323
WHY AREN'T YOU
WEARING BLUE?

20:56.356 --> 20:58.691
WHO READS THOSE THINGS?

20:58.725 --> 21:01.661
OBVIOUSLY
EVERYONE BUT YOU.

21:01.694 --> 21:05.298
MAYBE IF YOU SHUT UP,
NO ONE WILL NOTICE.

21:05.332 --> 21:07.900
* COME ON, JACKIE CHAN,
OH-OH-OH-OH... *

21:11.404 --> 21:13.039
[CHEERING]

21:17.744 --> 21:19.912
I AM A RECYCLING BIN.

21:19.946 --> 21:22.415
I NEED LOVE.

21:22.449 --> 21:23.883
YEAH!
WHOO!

21:23.916 --> 21:26.553
I NEED TRASH.
YEAH!

21:26.586 --> 21:30.657
IF EVERYBODY WOULD JUST
GIVE ME THEIR PAPER CUPS
AND PLATES,

21:30.690 --> 21:33.025
NOT ONLY WILL WE HAVE
A CLEANER DANCE FLOOR...

21:33.059 --> 21:35.428
I'M GETTING
A BONER.

21:35.462 --> 21:37.730
BUT AN ECOLOGICAL ONE. TOO.

21:37.764 --> 21:40.433
AND I'LL BE HAPPY.

21:40.467 --> 21:42.301
[CHEERING]

21:44.704 --> 21:45.905
Principal:
THANK YOU.

21:45.938 --> 21:48.841
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR YOUR ENTHUSIASM.

21:48.875 --> 21:51.611
I SEE THAT THE TIME
HAS COME TO ANNOUNCE

21:51.644 --> 21:52.912
WHO YOU'VE
ELECTED...

21:52.945 --> 21:54.414
AS YOUR KING
AND QUEEN

21:54.447 --> 21:56.949
FOR YOUR
FRESHMAN WINTER
BALL THIS YEAR.

21:56.983 --> 21:59.586
I THINK WE KNOW WHO THE KING
OF THE WINTER BALL
IS THIS YEAR, DON'T WE?

21:59.619 --> 22:00.920
HEY, IT'S NOT
IN THE BAG,

22:00.953 --> 22:03.423
BUT I THINK
I GOT THE VOTES
I WANTED.

22:03.456 --> 22:05.425
AND TO DO THAT,

22:05.458 --> 22:08.528
HERE IS YOUR FRESHMAN
CLASS PRESIDENT,
RICK SANFORD!

22:08.561 --> 22:10.630
[CHEERING]

22:11.998 --> 22:14.033
WHOO!

22:17.437 --> 22:19.906
HA HA HA!

22:19.939 --> 22:21.941
THANK YOU,
PRINCIPAL METCALF.

22:21.974 --> 22:24.777
THE THEME FOR
THIS YEAR'S FRESHMAN
WINTER BALL

22:24.811 --> 22:25.878
IS COURAGE.

22:25.912 --> 22:28.080
WE'RE GOING
TO NEED COURAGE

22:28.114 --> 22:29.949
TO FACE
NEW CHALLENGES,

22:29.982 --> 22:31.751
NEW PEOPLE,
OUR FUTURE.

22:31.784 --> 22:34.387
LET'S MAKE IT
A MEMORY

22:34.421 --> 22:35.588
NONE OF US
WILL EVER FORGET.

22:35.622 --> 22:36.856
[APPLAUSE]

22:36.889 --> 22:38.057
[MOCK RETCHING]

22:38.090 --> 22:41.027
AND NOW...

22:41.060 --> 22:43.963
I AM PLEASED TO ANNOUNCE
THAT THIS YEAR'S FRESHMAN
WINTER BALL QUEEN...

22:43.996 --> 22:45.765
WILL BE...

22:48.835 --> 22:49.969
MELISSA LEFEVRE.

22:50.002 --> 22:51.871
[CHEERING]

22:51.904 --> 22:53.806
OH, MY GOD.

22:55.174 --> 22:56.976
OW! OW!

22:57.009 --> 22:58.911
SORRY.

22:58.945 --> 23:01.514
Rick: COME ON UP.
WILL MELISSA COME
TO THE STAGE, PLEASE?

23:01.548 --> 23:02.682
COME ON.

23:15.027 --> 23:17.497
AND NOW YOUR VICE-PRESIDENT,
JODY COLE, WILL ANNOUNCE...

23:17.530 --> 23:19.666
WHO THIS YEAR'S
WINTER BALL KING WILL BE.

23:19.699 --> 23:21.100
[CHEERING]

23:21.133 --> 23:24.837
OW!
JODY!

23:24.871 --> 23:25.838
WHOO!
OKEY-DOKEY.

23:25.872 --> 23:27.073
HERE YOU GO.

23:28.808 --> 23:32.011
OK... UM...

23:32.044 --> 23:36.883
OK. AND THIS YEAR'S
WINTER BALL KING IS...

23:36.916 --> 23:41.854
Both: NOT RICK! NOT RICK!
NOT RICK! NOT RICK!

23:41.888 --> 23:43.856
UH--
[LAUGHS WEAKLY]

23:43.890 --> 23:46.859
UH--ANGUS BETHUNE?

23:46.893 --> 23:48.094
Both: ALL RIGHT!

23:54.601 --> 23:56.168
HOLY SHIT!

23:57.937 --> 23:59.138
[WHEEZING LAUGH]

23:59.171 --> 24:00.640
[JODY LAUGHS WEAKLY]

24:00.673 --> 24:03.476
Jody: WOULD ANGUS BETHUNE

24:03.510 --> 24:05.812
PLEASE COME UP
TO THE STAGE?

24:05.845 --> 24:07.780
PLEASE?

24:13.019 --> 24:14.153
[FIRE ALARM]

24:16.222 --> 24:20.893
Principal: SINGLE FILE.
BE ORDERLY, NOW. ORDERLY.

24:20.927 --> 24:23.696
SINGLE FILE.
NO MORE THROWING, ALL RIGHT...

24:23.730 --> 24:25.064
[RINGING CONTINUES]

24:25.097 --> 24:28.067
EXIT IN AN ORDERLY
FASHION! NO THROWING.

24:28.100 --> 24:29.869
Girl: WHAT A JOKE.

24:29.902 --> 24:34.574
ORDERLY FASHION. AH!
WATCH THAT OVER THERE.

24:34.607 --> 24:37.009
NO THROWING! NO THROWING.
I GOT YOUR NAMES.

24:44.617 --> 24:47.119
Angus, voice-over: OK,
IT WAS A JOKE. I KNEW THAT.

24:47.153 --> 24:49.221
AND A HELL OF A GOOD ONE, TOO.

24:49.255 --> 24:50.957
BUT LIKE MY GRANDFATHER SAYS,

24:50.990 --> 24:53.159
"LAUGH WITH 'EM, AND THEY
CAN'T LAUGH AT YOU."

25:02.168 --> 25:04.236
THANKS.

25:04.270 --> 25:05.872
YOU'RE WELCOME.

25:09.976 --> 25:11.911
BUDS.
BUDS.

25:11.944 --> 25:13.580
I'M NOT GOING.

25:13.613 --> 25:14.947
WHY NOT?

25:14.981 --> 25:17.249
WHY NOT? WHY NOT?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, WHY NOT?

25:17.283 --> 25:19.786
I MEAN WHY NOT?

25:19.819 --> 25:22.789
COME ON. YOU GET
TO DANCE WITH
MELISSA LEFEVRE.

25:22.822 --> 25:25.725
I'D SELL
BODY PARTS FOR
A CHANCE LIKE THAT.

25:25.758 --> 25:30.963
TROY, MELISSA LEFEVRE'S
PROBABLY SOMEWHERE PUKING
HER GUTS OUT RIGHT NOW.

25:30.997 --> 25:32.164
ANGUS.

25:32.198 --> 25:33.900
I'M NOT GOING.

25:33.933 --> 25:34.967
ANGUS.

25:35.001 --> 25:36.202
I'M NOT GOING!

25:36.235 --> 25:37.570
MELISSA.

25:47.179 --> 25:49.816
Angus, voice-over:
IN ALL THE YEARS I'D
KNOWN MELISSA LEFEVRE,

25:49.849 --> 25:52.084
I'D NEVER ACTUALLY
SPOKEN TO HER...

25:53.319 --> 25:55.221
"LATE FOR CLASS?" NO.

25:58.658 --> 26:00.226
"HEY, HOW ARE YOU DOIN'?"

26:02.695 --> 26:04.797
"HEY, MELISSA, RIGHT?" DUH!
OF COURSE SHE'S MELISSA!

26:17.043 --> 26:18.645
AND AT THAT MOMENT

26:18.678 --> 26:20.947
I REALIZED
I PROBABLY NEVER WOULD.

26:27.687 --> 26:29.689
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

26:29.722 --> 26:33.693
* I'M INFLAMED WITH DESIRE, AND
IT'S SPREADING LIKE WILDFIRE *

26:33.726 --> 26:38.197
* SHE DOESN'T KNOW IT,
BUT SHE'LL SOON BE MINE *

26:38.230 --> 26:43.202
* IT'S JUST
A QUESTION OF TIME *

26:43.235 --> 26:45.204
* RUBELLA

26:45.237 --> 26:50.877
* I'M INSANELY OBSESSED,
AND I SIMPLY WILL NOT REST *

26:50.910 --> 26:55.748
* SHE DOESN'T KNOW IT YET,
BUT SHE'S THE ONE *

26:55.782 --> 26:57.183
Angus, voice-over:
I COULDN'T HELP BUT WONDER

26:57.216 --> 26:59.218
WHAT MELISSA LEFEVRE
WAS THINKING.

26:59.251 --> 27:01.721
SHE'D BE AT THE DANCE
WITH RICK, OF COURSE,

27:01.754 --> 27:04.891
SO HER "WINTER NIGHTMARE
ON ELM STREET" WOULD LAST
BUT A FEW MINUTES AT MOST.

27:04.924 --> 27:08.060
SHE'D PROBABLY TELL HERSELF,
"IT'S LIKE A TRIP
TO THE DENTIST.

27:08.094 --> 27:10.730
"NO MATTER HOW BADLY
HE'S GONNA HURT ME,

27:10.763 --> 27:12.832
NO MATTER HOW MANY
BARE NERVES HE DRILLS,

27:12.865 --> 27:14.734
"IN AN HOUR
I'LL BE OUT OF THERE,

27:14.767 --> 27:16.736
AND I'LL STILL BE ALIVE."

27:16.769 --> 27:20.873
OF COURSE, MELISSA
HADN'T SEEN ME DANCE.

27:20.907 --> 27:24.343
Troy: WHEN YOU WANT SOMETHING,
YOU HAVE TO MOTIVATE YOURSELF.

27:27.747 --> 27:30.082
MOTIVATION.

27:32.384 --> 27:36.989
LITTLE STOMACH MUSCLES
ABOVE THE BELLY BUTTON.

27:37.023 --> 27:39.258
TINY BLONDE HAIRS...

27:39.291 --> 27:41.360
ON LONG...

27:41.393 --> 27:45.464
ATHLETIC...THIGHS.

27:45.497 --> 27:48.334
SHE DOES HAVE
GREAT LITTLE
STOMACH MUSCLES.

27:50.436 --> 27:53.039
HOW AM I GONNA
PULL THIS OFF?

27:53.072 --> 27:55.107
WE'RE GONNA TURN YOU...

27:55.141 --> 27:57.409
FROM A LARGE,
PATHETIC VIRGIN...

27:57.443 --> 28:01.213
INTO A LARGE, PATHETIC
VIRGIN WITH A NEW LOOK!

28:04.751 --> 28:06.185
WE'LL EXPERIMENT.

28:07.453 --> 28:09.088
[SNORING]

28:26.338 --> 28:27.974
[NEEDLE DROPS ON RECORD]

28:28.007 --> 28:31.811
[TRUMPET PLAYING "REVEILLE"]

28:31.844 --> 28:32.812
[NEEDLE SCRATCHES]

28:32.845 --> 28:35.381
I WAS AWAKE,
DAMN IT!

28:39.786 --> 28:41.921
IT'S TIME TO TAKE YOUR PILL.

28:41.954 --> 28:43.355
WHERE'S MY VEST?

28:45.357 --> 28:47.193
[COUGHING]

28:50.496 --> 28:53.299
I HAVE TO GO
TO THIS DANCE AT SCHOOL.

28:53.332 --> 28:55.434
I'M THE WINTER BALL KING.

28:55.467 --> 28:57.036
THAT'S GOOD.

28:57.069 --> 29:00.239
FOR A LAUGH. IT WAS A JOKE.

29:00.272 --> 29:04.210
THIS HAVE ANYTHING
TO DO WITH THAT...

29:04.243 --> 29:06.378
QUARTERBACK?

29:06.412 --> 29:08.414
I SHOULD'VE
BROKEN HIS NOSE.

29:08.447 --> 29:10.416
YOU CAN'T GO AROUND
BEATIN' EVERYBODY UP

29:10.449 --> 29:12.018
JUST 'CAUSE
THEY DON'T LIKE YOU.

29:12.051 --> 29:13.452
USE WHAT YOU HAVE
IN HERE.

29:13.485 --> 29:17.556
YOU HAVE A BIG
HEART, ANGUS.

29:17.589 --> 29:20.226
I HAVE A FAT HEART,
GRANDPA.

29:20.259 --> 29:22.094
I CAN'T DANCE.

29:24.430 --> 29:28.400
I EVER TELL YOU
ABOUT THE IRISH SWOON?

29:28.434 --> 29:31.370
THE IRISH SWOON
IS AN OLD FAMILY SECRET.

29:31.403 --> 29:32.872
YOU'RE ON
THE DANCE FLOOR, SEE?

29:32.905 --> 29:36.042
YOU CRADLE YOUR GIRL
IN YOUR ARMS.

29:36.075 --> 29:37.476
CRUSH HER RIBS.

29:37.509 --> 29:38.577
AND THEN...

29:38.610 --> 29:40.880
YOU SWEEP HER BACK.

29:40.913 --> 29:42.882
AND SNAP HER NECK.

29:42.915 --> 29:45.885
THEN YOU KISS HER.

29:45.918 --> 29:48.387
YEAH. AND THEN SHE'S
TRAUMATIZED FOR LIFE

29:48.420 --> 29:50.156
AND GOES ON A SHOOTING SPREE,

29:50.189 --> 29:51.523
KILLING LARGE PEOPLE.

29:51.557 --> 29:54.126
ANGUS, SHUT UP.

29:57.596 --> 29:59.832
[HORN HONKING]

29:59.866 --> 30:03.469
NOW, THE KEY TO
THE IRISH SWOON...

30:03.502 --> 30:05.537
IS TO DO IT IN
ONE SMOOTH MOTION

30:05.571 --> 30:07.974
BEFORE SHE GETS A CHANCE
TO REALIZE WHAT HIT HER.

30:08.007 --> 30:09.976
THAT'S HOW
I NABBED APRIL.

30:10.009 --> 30:11.377
[HONKS HORN]

30:11.410 --> 30:13.412
GRANDPA, I WILL NEVER, EVER,
IN MY ENTIRE LIFE...

30:13.445 --> 30:17.416
GET A CHANCE TO KISS
MELISSA LEFEVRE'S DOG,
LET ALONE MELISSA.

30:17.449 --> 30:19.485
WHY THE HELL NOT?

30:19.518 --> 30:21.020
BECAUSE FIRST OF ALL,
I CAN'T TOUCH HER.

30:21.053 --> 30:22.354
WHY THE HELL NOT?
HI, TROY.

30:22.388 --> 30:24.356
SWEAT! HI, TROY.
HEY.

30:24.390 --> 30:25.557
EVERYBODY SWEATS.

30:25.591 --> 30:27.059
NOT LIKE ME.

30:27.093 --> 30:28.928
I DON'T SWEAT, I RAIN.

30:28.961 --> 30:30.930
THAT'S GROSS!

30:30.963 --> 30:34.000
YOU THINK
SOMETHING'S GROSS?

30:34.033 --> 30:38.104
YOU WANT GROSS?
TOUCH ANGUS' HEAD.

30:38.137 --> 30:39.271
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

30:39.305 --> 30:41.874
YOUR HAIR LOOKS
RIDICULOUS.

30:41.908 --> 30:43.943
IT WAS AN EXPERIMENT,
DAMN IT.

30:43.976 --> 30:44.944
[CRINKLING]

30:44.977 --> 30:46.378
YEAH.

30:51.483 --> 30:53.352
Grandpa: ANGUS...

30:53.385 --> 30:55.121
THIS IS
MADAME RULENSKA.

30:55.154 --> 30:58.024
SHE IS GOING TO TEACH YOU
HOW TO CUT A RUG.

31:01.627 --> 31:06.232
DRIFT WITH THE CURRENT
OF YOUR FEELINGS...

31:06.265 --> 31:09.135
AND MOVE WITH ME.

31:09.168 --> 31:12.604
ARE YOU READY?
GOOD.

31:12.638 --> 31:13.973
AND--

31:14.006 --> 31:15.574
Singer: * FIESTA, HA HA!
[RIP]

31:15.607 --> 31:18.144
Rulenska:
MY SCARF!

31:18.177 --> 31:19.478
WHAT?

31:19.511 --> 31:21.981
GET YOUR FOOT
OFF THE SCARF!
WHAT?

31:22.014 --> 31:24.984
GET YOUR FOOT OFF--

31:25.017 --> 31:29.121
Singer: * YES, GIRLS

31:29.155 --> 31:31.457
[CHUCKLES WEAKLY]

31:31.490 --> 31:32.624
* ME MIND ON FIRE...

31:32.658 --> 31:35.161
ALL RIGHT.
START. 1, 2, 3, UH!

31:35.194 --> 31:37.163
1 AND 2 AND 3, UH!

31:37.196 --> 31:39.598
OH, THAT'S VERY GOOD. YES.

31:39.631 --> 31:41.200
OH, WAIT A MINUTE.
THAT'S BAD.

31:41.233 --> 31:43.335
* ALL AROUND ME
FEELIN' HOT, HOT, HOT... *

31:43.369 --> 31:45.537
[CLANK]

31:45.571 --> 31:46.572
AND--

31:46.605 --> 31:48.140
[CRUNCH]

31:48.174 --> 31:49.341
* ON A NIGHT LIKE THIS

31:49.375 --> 31:50.342
* AIN'T IT SWEET

31:50.376 --> 31:52.344
ON THE FEET!

31:52.378 --> 31:54.680
Grandpa: SCREW 'EM, ANGUS.
JUST DANCE!

31:56.682 --> 31:57.950
YOU'RE DANCIN',
ANGUS.

31:57.984 --> 31:58.951
* FEELIN' HOT, HOT, HOT...

31:58.985 --> 32:00.019
YOU'RE DANCIN'!

32:00.052 --> 32:01.120
* OH, LORD...

32:02.688 --> 32:04.023
[SINGER LAUGHS]

32:04.056 --> 32:05.024
OHH!

32:09.228 --> 32:11.530
[MUZAK PLAYING]

32:11.563 --> 32:14.600
Man: IT'S THE BIGGEST SIZE
WE HAVE LEFT IN BLACK.

32:14.633 --> 32:17.203
I WANT BLACK.

32:17.236 --> 32:19.071
Grandpa:
WHAT ELSE DO YOU HAVE?

32:19.105 --> 32:23.442
I HAVE ONE
OTHER THING IN HIS SIZE,
BUT IT ISN'T BLACK.

32:23.475 --> 32:24.610
I WANT BLACK!

32:26.712 --> 32:28.214
WE'LL GIVE IT A TRY.

32:28.247 --> 32:32.018
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

32:37.423 --> 32:38.557
[BLOWS]

32:41.460 --> 32:42.728
[SNIFFS]

32:42.761 --> 32:44.230
OHH!

32:51.603 --> 32:53.405
THIS SHOULD FIT.

32:53.439 --> 32:55.607
IT'S PURPLE.

32:55.641 --> 32:57.376
IT'S PLUM.

32:57.409 --> 32:58.377
IT'S CLASSY.

32:58.410 --> 33:00.179
Both: IT'S PLUM.

33:00.212 --> 33:02.248
IT'S YOUR SIZE.

33:02.281 --> 33:03.315
Angus: EVERYONE
WILL BE WEARING BLACK.

33:03.349 --> 33:05.084
Grandpa:
YOU'LL BE DIFFERENT.

33:05.117 --> 33:06.585
THAT'S TRUE.

33:06.618 --> 33:10.089
I DON'T WANT
TO BE DIFFERENT.
I WANT NORMAL.

33:10.122 --> 33:12.258
I WANT
SOCIALLY ACCEPTABLE.

33:12.291 --> 33:15.061
I WANT A BLACK TUXEDO.

33:15.094 --> 33:17.429
IT'LL LOOK GREAT ON YOU.

33:17.463 --> 33:19.265
AND AS FOR WHAT ANYBODY
ELSE THINKS,

33:19.298 --> 33:21.767
ALWAYS REMEMBER THESE WORDS
AND LIVE BY 'EM:

33:21.800 --> 33:24.603
"SCREW 'EM!"
HE'LL TRY IT ON.

33:24.636 --> 33:26.438
NO, HE WON'T.

33:26.472 --> 33:27.539
PUT IT
IN THE DRESSING ROOM.

33:27.573 --> 33:28.807
Angus:
PUT IT ON A RACK.

33:28.840 --> 33:31.210
PUT IT ON A DEAD
GUY AND BURY IT.

33:32.678 --> 33:34.280
["RIDE OF
THE VALKYRIES" PLAYING]

33:34.313 --> 33:35.747
[IMITATING WOMAN'S VOICE]
HELLO, BIG BOY.

33:35.781 --> 33:37.783
WHAT THE HELL
IS THAT?

33:39.218 --> 33:41.653
THIS IS WANDA.

33:41.687 --> 33:43.222
WANDA?

33:44.556 --> 33:46.458
MY DAD USED TO HAVE HER
IN HIS WAITING ROOM,

33:46.492 --> 33:50.129
BUT SHE KIND OF
SCARED ALL THE KIDS.
YOU KNOW.

33:50.162 --> 33:52.798
I'LL BET.

33:52.831 --> 33:55.301
AND SHE IS WHAT,
YOUR DATE?

33:55.334 --> 33:58.270
ACTUALLY, SHE'S YOURS.

33:58.304 --> 34:00.439
[ROCK SONG STARTS]

34:09.181 --> 34:12.484
* I'M THINKING ABOUT

34:12.518 --> 34:15.654
* ASKING YOU TO BE

34:15.687 --> 34:16.822
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

34:16.855 --> 34:18.456
I'M TAPING THIS.

34:18.489 --> 34:20.159
GET OUT OF HERE.

34:20.192 --> 34:22.228
ANGUS, IT'S WHAT JOCKS DO

34:22.261 --> 34:23.829
SO THEY CAN SEE WHERE
THEY'RE MAKING MISTAKES.

34:23.862 --> 34:25.164
FORGET IT.

34:25.197 --> 34:28.134
ANGUS, THE DANCE
IS ON THE 22nd.

34:28.167 --> 34:30.536
YOU'VE GOT
TWO AND A HALF WEEKS, BUD.

34:30.569 --> 34:35.206
NO ONE SEES THE
TAPE, AND YOU DON'T
TELL YOUR MOTHER?

34:35.241 --> 34:36.608
I DON'T TELL HER
EVERYTHING.

34:40.545 --> 34:42.514
* AND I'D RATHER

34:42.547 --> 34:46.217
* BE TOO YOUNG
THAN TOO OLD *

34:46.252 --> 34:48.587
LOOK UNDER HER SHIRT.

34:48.620 --> 34:52.858
HEY, SHE'S
ANATOMICALLY CORRECT.

34:52.891 --> 34:54.659
OW! HEY, WATCH IT!

34:56.395 --> 34:59.331
HEY, A GIRL'S BOD
IS A GIRL'S BOD.

34:59.365 --> 35:02.534
THERE'S MORE TO GIRLS
THAN JUST THEIR BODS, GEEK.

35:02.568 --> 35:04.236
RIGHT. AND YOU GO NUTS
FOR MELISSA

35:04.270 --> 35:06.805
BECAUSE OF HER GRADES?

35:06.838 --> 35:09.708
* LOOK AT
ALL THE THINGS... *

35:09.741 --> 35:13.212
Angus: SHE'S BEAUTIFUL, OK?

35:13.245 --> 35:15.181
THERE'S
SOMETHING ABOUT HER.

35:16.748 --> 35:19.385
HER BOD, BUD.

35:19.418 --> 35:21.887
[SCOFFS]
NO, TROY.

35:21.920 --> 35:23.855
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS.

35:23.889 --> 35:26.692
I GET THE WORST
PAIN IN MY STOMACH
WHENEVER I SEE HER.

35:27.859 --> 35:31.397
YOU GET A BONER
IN YOUR STOMACH?

35:31.430 --> 35:32.764
OW! HEY!

35:32.798 --> 35:36.302
YOU'RE SUCH A GOOD DANCER.

35:36.335 --> 35:39.405
HA HA! THANKS.

35:39.438 --> 35:40.739
NOT YOU.

35:40.772 --> 35:43.742
[TROY SPEAKING ON VIDEOTAPE]

35:43.775 --> 35:45.311
DO YOU WANT
TO BE ALONE?

35:45.344 --> 35:48.647
[LAUGHING ON RECORDING]

35:48.680 --> 35:51.417
THIS WAS MY IDEA.

35:51.450 --> 35:53.585
[ANGUS ON TAPE]
DO I LOOK STUPID?

35:53.619 --> 35:55.421
CAN I TAKE HER HOME?

35:55.454 --> 35:59.258
[SONG PLAYING ON VIDEOTAPE]

35:59.291 --> 36:01.293
JUST FOR A WEEK.

36:01.327 --> 36:02.861
[NEW SONG STARTS]

36:02.894 --> 36:05.797
* MY FRIEND DROVE OFF
THE OTHER DAY *

36:05.831 --> 36:08.200
* NOW HE'S GONE
AND ALL THEY SAY *

36:08.234 --> 36:11.737
* IS YOU GOT TO LIVE
'CAUSE LIFE GOES ON *

36:13.639 --> 36:16.575
* AND NOW I SEE
I'M MORTAL, TOO *

36:16.608 --> 36:18.844
* I CAN'T LIVE MY LIFE
LIKE YOU *

36:18.877 --> 36:22.581
* GOT TO LIVE IT UP
WHILE LIFE GOES ON *

36:24.716 --> 36:27.619
* AND I THINK
IT'S ALL RIGHT *

36:27.653 --> 36:29.621
* THAT I DO WHAT I LIKE

36:29.655 --> 36:32.891
* 'CAUSE THAT'S THE WAY
I WANNA LIVE *

36:32.924 --> 36:35.627
* IT'S HOW I GIVE

36:35.661 --> 36:38.564
* AND I'M STILL GIVIN'

36:41.567 --> 36:44.703
* AND NOW I WONDER
'BOUT MY FRIEND *

36:44.736 --> 36:47.273
* IF HE GAVE
ALL HE COULD GIVE *

36:47.306 --> 36:50.709
* 'CAUSE HE LIVED HIS LIFE
LIKE I LIVE MINE *

36:52.578 --> 36:55.447
* IF YOU COULD SEE
INSIDE MY HEAD *

36:55.481 --> 36:57.849
* THEN YOU'D START
TO UNDERSTAND *

36:57.883 --> 37:00.886
* THE THINGS I VALUE
IN MY HEART *

37:03.755 --> 37:06.725
* AND I THINK
IT'S ALL RIGHT *

37:06.758 --> 37:08.660
* THAT I DO WHAT I LIKE...

37:08.694 --> 37:10.962
Man on radio: OK, WE'RE
HERE AT RADIO OWATONNA.

37:10.996 --> 37:12.831
AND WE GOT ANOTHER
WINNER HERE.

37:12.864 --> 37:14.633
TWO TICKETS
AND BACKSTAGE PASSES

37:14.666 --> 37:17.969
FOR THE UPCOMING GREEN DAY
CONCERT FOR RICK SANFORD.

37:18.003 --> 37:20.506
TELL US HOW YOU WON, RICK.

37:20.539 --> 37:22.674
Rick on radio: HEY, GREAT!
YOU KNOW, I WAS JUST
WALKIN' BY A PHONE BOOTH...

37:22.708 --> 37:25.711
AND I HEARD THIS SONG COME
OVER THIS GUY'S CAR RADIO,
SO I DECIDED TO CALL.

37:25.744 --> 37:26.978
[COIN DROPS]

37:27.012 --> 37:30.682
HEY! I JUST GOT
MY QUARTER BACK!

37:30.716 --> 37:31.983
[CRASH]

37:34.386 --> 37:36.021
[BELL RINGING]

37:41.026 --> 37:43.662
OH, HEY, IT'S BIG RED.
WHERE'S THE TUBSTER?

37:43.695 --> 37:45.531
I CAN'T WAIT
TO SEE HIM ON
THE DANCE FLOOR.

37:45.564 --> 37:47.799
YEAH. WATCH ALL THAT
LARD SHAKIN' AROUND.

37:47.833 --> 37:49.668
[TROY COUGHING]

37:51.570 --> 37:53.305
Short football player:
THIS SHOULD BE COOL.

37:53.339 --> 37:56.608
ANGUS IS GONNA BLOW
YOUR BONEHEAD FACE
OFF THE DANCE FLOOR.

38:00.912 --> 38:02.981
[LAUGHTER]

38:06.918 --> 38:08.554
WHEN ANGUS DANCES
WITH MELISSA,

38:08.587 --> 38:10.822
SHE'S NEVER GONNA LOOK BACK.

38:10.856 --> 38:13.091
ANGUS CAN DANCE?

38:13.124 --> 38:14.560
YEAH.

38:14.593 --> 38:17.563
THAT SUCKS.

38:17.596 --> 38:18.797
Tall football player:
YEAH, REALLY.

38:18.830 --> 38:21.433
WHAT IF HE'S
REALLY GOOD?

38:21.467 --> 38:23.869
I MEAN, ALL YOU
CAN DO IS THAT...

38:25.704 --> 38:27.105
WHITE THING.

38:27.138 --> 38:28.607
SHUT UP!

38:28.640 --> 38:30.809
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
IF HE CAN REALLY DANCE?

38:30.842 --> 38:31.877
I MEAN...

38:31.910 --> 38:33.645
I DON'T KNOW.

38:35.080 --> 38:37.416
LOOK, SOMETHING, OK?

38:39.618 --> 38:41.119
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

38:41.152 --> 38:43.422
LET ME GO! COME ON!

38:43.455 --> 38:44.990
THANKS FOR THE TIP.

38:46.425 --> 38:47.726
Rick: YOU KNOW, UM,

38:47.759 --> 38:48.927
YOU REALLY SHOULDN'T
HANG AROUND THE HALLS

38:48.960 --> 38:50.662
WITHOUT A PASS.

38:50.696 --> 38:52.964
Short football player:
HEY, KEEP THIS
TO YOURSELF, SQUAT.

38:52.998 --> 38:54.065
Tall football player:
YEAH. HEH HEH.

38:54.099 --> 38:56.435
Rick:
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

38:56.468 --> 38:58.437
OK.

38:58.470 --> 38:59.771
YOU ARE SUCH A LOSER.

38:59.805 --> 39:01.440
DUDE, YOU COULDN'T HIT
THE SIDE OF A BARN.

39:01.473 --> 39:03.074
Troy: AND, LIKE,
HE CAME DOWN.
AND THEY CAPTURED HIM,

39:03.108 --> 39:04.943
AND THEY, LIKE,
CHAINED HIM UP...

39:04.976 --> 39:07.078
AND THEY CUT OFF
HIS ARMS AND LEGS
SO HE CAN'T GET AWAY.

39:07.112 --> 39:08.780
AND THEY TOOK, LIKE,
THIS METAL ROD

39:08.814 --> 39:09.948
AND THEY STICK IT
INTO HIS HEAD.

39:09.981 --> 39:11.617
AND IT, LIKE, SUCKS OUT
HIS BRAINS,

39:11.650 --> 39:14.786
REPLACES IT WITH,
LIKE, THIS GREEN
GLOWING OOZE...

39:14.820 --> 39:17.823
SO IT CAN TAKE
OVER HIS BODY. I MEAN,
IT'S SO COOL...

39:25.130 --> 39:28.600
WEDBERG! HIT THE SHOWERS!

39:28.634 --> 39:30.902
I'VE GOT A NOTE
FROM MY DOCTOR.

39:39.678 --> 39:42.748
IT'S UPSIDE DOWN,
WEDBERG.

39:42.781 --> 39:44.115
THIS IS FROM YOUR FATHER.

39:44.149 --> 39:45.517
HE'S A DOCTOR.

39:45.551 --> 39:47.886
HE'S A DENTIST.

39:47.919 --> 39:50.121
I HAVE SORE GUMS.

39:50.155 --> 39:52.658
SHOWER!

39:52.691 --> 39:55.026
EVERY DAY I GO THROUGH
THIS WITH THIS KID.

39:57.162 --> 40:00.499
HEY, MY SHIRT'S GONE.

40:00.532 --> 40:01.800
YOU'RE A REAL
ASSHOLE, SANFORD.

40:01.833 --> 40:03.101
DID I SAY THAT?

40:03.134 --> 40:04.703
Short football player:
TOUGH GUY.

40:04.736 --> 40:06.672
HEY, IT'S
THE BUTTERBALL KING.

40:06.705 --> 40:08.440
JUST GIVE HIM HIS SHIRT BACK.

40:08.474 --> 40:09.608
TROY.

40:09.641 --> 40:11.443
OH, YOU LOSE
YOUR SHIRT, MAN?

40:11.477 --> 40:13.479
LIKE YOU DIDN'T KNOW.

40:13.512 --> 40:15.447
LISTEN, ANGUS,
I'D LEND YOU MY SHIRT,

40:15.481 --> 40:17.148
BUT I'M AFRAID
IT'S NOT GONNA FIT.

40:17.182 --> 40:19.518
IT MIGHT RIP ON YOU.

40:19.551 --> 40:24.022
Troy: THAT'S 'CAUSE IT'S
CHEAP, LIKE YOUR MOTHER.

40:24.055 --> 40:26.157
WHOO!
OOH.

40:28.627 --> 40:29.895
Troy: HEY,
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN'?

40:29.928 --> 40:31.863
LET ME GO! LET ME GO!

40:31.897 --> 40:37.202
LET ME GO! QUIT IT!
OW! OW! QUIT IT!

40:37.235 --> 40:39.471
OW!

40:39.505 --> 40:41.773
I WANT MY SHIRT BACK.

40:41.807 --> 40:44.109
MAYBE YOU LOST IT.

40:44.142 --> 40:47.178
Troy: DON'T HIT HIM, ANGUS.
YOU'LL GET EXPELLED!

40:48.914 --> 40:50.549
IF HE STILL WANTS
TO GO TO THE DANCE
AFTER ALL THIS,

40:50.582 --> 40:51.650
GOOD FOR HIM.

40:51.683 --> 40:53.251
YOU KNOW, HE WON
FAIR AND SQUARE.

40:53.284 --> 40:55.053
I KNOW YOU SET IT UP!

40:55.086 --> 40:57.689
HEY, IT WAS
A LITTLE JOKE, OK?

40:57.723 --> 40:59.558
YOU SHOULD BE
THANKING ME.
I MEAN,

40:59.591 --> 41:01.727
THIS IS THE CHANCE
YOU'VE WANTED YOUR
WHOLE LIFE, RIGHT?

41:01.760 --> 41:04.195
NOW IT'S YOURS.
I'M THE ONE GETTING
THE SHAFT THIS TIME.

41:04.229 --> 41:08.567
MELISSA'S BITCHIN'
MY EAR OUT 'CAUSE SHE'S
GOT TO DANCE WITH YOU.

41:08.600 --> 41:12.203
HEY, YOU KNOW, I MEAN,
NOTHING PERSONAL.

41:14.305 --> 41:17.208
[KNOCKING ON LOCKER DOOR]

41:17.242 --> 41:19.611
Troy: COME ON.
LET ME OUT!

41:19.645 --> 41:21.580
[SNIFFLING]

41:21.613 --> 41:24.249
YOU KNOW, IT DOESN'T
SMELL SO BAD IN HERE.

41:29.621 --> 41:30.922
EASY. EASY.

41:43.969 --> 41:45.236
HE TOOK
MY UNDERWEAR, TOO.

41:45.270 --> 41:48.674
SCREW RICK
AND SCREW THE DANCE!

41:48.707 --> 41:50.876
HE'S JUST GONNA DO
SOMETHING TO YOU.

41:55.146 --> 41:58.016
SO WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA DO?

41:58.049 --> 41:59.618
GO TO CLASS
WITHOUT UNDERWEAR.

41:59.651 --> 42:00.719
[ZIPS UP]

42:00.752 --> 42:03.989
OH, CAREFUL!

42:04.022 --> 42:05.857
[EXCITED CHATTER, LAUGHTER]

42:07.659 --> 42:08.727
Boy: WHERE IS IT?

42:08.760 --> 42:09.928
Second boy:
RIGHT UP THERE.

42:09.961 --> 42:11.229
Third boy: NO WAY!

42:11.262 --> 42:12.230
[GIRL LAUGHING]

42:12.263 --> 42:13.765
Girl: OH, WOW!

42:13.799 --> 42:15.100
ANGUS?

42:15.133 --> 42:16.635
WHAT?

42:16.668 --> 42:19.204
I THINK I KNOW WHAT RICK
DID WITH YOUR UNDERWEAR.

42:19.237 --> 42:21.272
Fourth boy: OH, WOW!

42:24.876 --> 42:25.844
Boy: HEY, CHECK IT OUT!

42:25.877 --> 42:27.012
I DON'T BELIEVE IT.

42:27.045 --> 42:28.914
YEAH...

42:34.052 --> 42:35.654
DO YOU BELIEVE IT?

42:35.687 --> 42:38.156
[HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
NO.

42:38.189 --> 42:40.992
YOUR UNDERWEAR IS ALMOST
AS BIG AS THE FLAG.

42:42.694 --> 42:45.964
Principal: BUFORD, GET
THAT DOWN FROM THERE.

42:50.268 --> 42:52.871
ANGUS, LOOK AT IT
THIS WAY.

42:52.904 --> 42:54.339
WHAT COULD BE WORSE?

42:59.210 --> 43:00.712
[GASPS]

43:05.884 --> 43:08.620
[MUFFLED MOANING]

43:17.062 --> 43:18.864
[GASPS]

43:18.897 --> 43:22.668
[RIFF OF "STAR-SPANGLED BANNER"
PLAYS ON SOUNDTRACK]

43:38.149 --> 43:39.718
Together: SHE DIDN'T SEE IT!
SHE DIDN'T SEE IT!

43:39.751 --> 43:41.019
SHE DIDN'T SEE IT!

43:41.052 --> 43:42.020
I DON'T BELIEVE IT!
YEAH...

43:42.053 --> 43:44.289
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH!
YES!

43:45.456 --> 43:47.292
Girl: HEY, MELISSA!

43:49.260 --> 43:51.362
[LAUGHTER]

43:51.396 --> 43:55.701
THAT'S WHAT YOU CALL
GETTING A SLICE
OF THE OLD DICK PIE.

44:00.405 --> 44:04.009
EVERYONE'S GONE, ANGUS.
CAN WE GO NOW?

44:04.042 --> 44:05.143
[SIGHS]

44:05.176 --> 44:07.378
Angus, voice-over:
I WAS PISSED.

44:07.412 --> 44:11.282
THAT WAS MY FAVORITE
PAIR OF UNDERWEAR.

44:11.316 --> 44:14.252
MAYBE NO ONE KNEW
THEY WERE YOURS.

44:14.285 --> 44:17.355
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU HAD
YOUR NAME PRINTED ALL OVER
THEM OR ANYTHING.

44:23.228 --> 44:24.896
HEY, MAN, I'M NOT THE ONE

44:24.930 --> 44:26.765
WHO PUT YOUR UNDERWEAR
ON THE FLAGPOLE.

44:26.798 --> 44:28.099
[LAUGHING]

44:28.133 --> 44:30.001
THAT WAS YOUR
UNDERWEAR, ANGUS?

44:30.035 --> 44:31.870
[LAUGHING]

44:36.975 --> 44:39.477
[VEHICLE ENGINE STARTS]

44:39.510 --> 44:41.346
[HORN HONKS]

44:43.148 --> 44:45.884
TROY...

44:45.917 --> 44:47.052
I'M--

44:54.459 --> 44:56.094
WHATEVER.

45:11.009 --> 45:12.043
WHAT?

45:15.013 --> 45:18.817
Rick: THE DANCE IS COMING UP,
AND WE REALLY WANT TO
PLAY A LITTLE JOKE ON ANGUS,

45:18.850 --> 45:20.451
BUT WE'RE KIND OF STUMPED
ON WHAT IT SHOULD BE.

45:20.485 --> 45:23.321
HOPING MAYBE
YOU COULD HELP US.

45:23.354 --> 45:25.991
GIVE ME A BREAK!

45:26.024 --> 45:27.793
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

45:27.826 --> 45:29.394
JUST GIVE US SOMETHING
WE CAN USE TO--

45:29.427 --> 45:31.429
TO EMBARRASS HIM
IN FRONT OF
THE WHOLE SCHOOL!

45:31.462 --> 45:33.031
FORGET IT!

45:34.866 --> 45:36.234
OW!

45:36.267 --> 45:39.237
LOOK, IT'S JUST
FOR FUN, MAN.

45:39.270 --> 45:41.306
Troy: I'M NOT
GONNA DO IT!

45:41.339 --> 45:42.841
OK.

45:44.209 --> 45:45.343
LET'S GO.

45:45.376 --> 45:46.477
Troy: HEY! LET ME GO!

45:46.511 --> 45:50.882
LET ME GO! LET ME--HELP!

45:50.916 --> 45:51.917
AAH!

45:51.950 --> 45:54.786
OW!

45:54.820 --> 45:56.187
COME ON, MAN. LET'S GO.

45:56.221 --> 46:00.358
[TROY SOBBING]

46:00.391 --> 46:01.827
Rick:
SEE? SEE, TOUGH GUY?

46:01.860 --> 46:04.029
MAN, WHAT THE HELL
IS YOUR PROBLEM?

46:04.062 --> 46:05.430
LOOK, JUST HELP US
OUT WITH THIS.

46:05.463 --> 46:07.098
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING.

46:07.132 --> 46:08.867
THEN GET SOMETHING,
ALL RIGHT?

46:08.900 --> 46:11.970
THIS IS IMPORTANT,
YOU UNDERSTAND?

46:14.906 --> 46:16.574
UNDERSTAND?

46:16.607 --> 46:18.877
[SPEAKING YIDDISH]

46:18.910 --> 46:20.946
ABSOLUTELY.

46:20.979 --> 46:22.213
WHAT ARE YOU
DOIN' HERE?

46:22.247 --> 46:24.382
DID YOU TAKE
YOUR PILL?

46:24.415 --> 46:26.117
INSIDE
COAT POCKET.

46:27.919 --> 46:28.887
ANGUS.

46:28.920 --> 46:30.455
WHAT?

46:30.488 --> 46:32.523
YOU'RE MAKING ME NERVOUS.

46:32.557 --> 46:36.194
THIS IS MY LAST DAY
AS A BACHELOR.
I NEED MY PEACE.

46:38.263 --> 46:40.231
WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM?

46:40.265 --> 46:41.900
RICK SANFORD.

46:41.933 --> 46:43.234
YOU BREAK THAT KID'S
NOSE AGAIN?

46:43.268 --> 46:44.903
I'M THINKING ABOUT IT.

46:44.936 --> 46:48.406
WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN ANOTHER QUARTERBACK
COMES ALONG?

46:48.439 --> 46:50.909
'CAUSE THERE'S ALWAYS
GONNA BE ANOTHER
QUARTERBACK, ANGUS.

46:50.942 --> 46:54.345
I'M SICK AND TIRED
OF HEARING THAT!
PEOPLE SUCK, GRANDPA.

46:54.379 --> 46:56.882
I COULD KNOCK THIS GUY OUT
WITH ONE PUNCH.

46:56.915 --> 46:59.284
FORGET IT.
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

47:01.586 --> 47:03.588
I DON'T UNDERSTAND?

47:03.621 --> 47:06.524
Angus: THAT'S WHY I WANTED
TO GO TO JEFFERSON, OK?

47:06.557 --> 47:08.426
BECAUSE NO ONE
WILL KNOW WHO I AM,

47:08.459 --> 47:10.461
AND IF NOBODY KNOWS WHO
I AM, I DON'T HAVE
TO BE ANGUS BETHUNE.

47:10.495 --> 47:12.931
I CAN'T GO TO THIS DANCE.

47:12.964 --> 47:14.866
YOU'RE A COWARD
IF YOU DON'T.

47:14.900 --> 47:18.436
I CAN'T DANCE.
I CAN'T TALK TO GIRLS.

47:18.469 --> 47:21.106
BUT I CAN SMASH
RICK SANFORD'S FACE IN.

47:21.139 --> 47:22.941
YOU'RE A COWARD
IF YOU DO.

47:22.974 --> 47:24.876
YOU THINK
I DON'T UNDERSTAND?

47:24.910 --> 47:26.978
YOU THINK I DON'T KNOW
WHAT PEOPLE ARE SAYING
ABOUT APRIL AND ME?

47:27.012 --> 47:30.315
SHE'S TOO YOUNG.
I'M TOO OLD. SCREW 'EM!

47:30.348 --> 47:32.550
YOU DON'T SEE ME
PUNCHING ANYBODY OUT.

47:32.583 --> 47:34.485
BECAUSE YOU'RE
A FOOL, GRANDPA,

47:34.519 --> 47:37.588
AND I'M TIRED OF
BEING ONE!

47:37.622 --> 47:39.958
I'M A FOOL, HUH?

47:39.991 --> 47:43.461
WELL, APRIL
DOESN'T THINK SO.

47:43.494 --> 47:45.296
AND I'M GETTING
MARRIED TOMORROW,

47:45.330 --> 47:47.966
AND I DON'T CARE
WHAT THE HELL ANYBODY
SAYS ABOUT IT.

47:47.999 --> 47:50.201
I NEED
MY MOMENT, DAMN IT!

47:56.507 --> 47:58.243
[SONG PLAYING ON RADIO]

48:14.659 --> 48:18.429
* SITTING BACK
AND DOING NOTHING *

48:18.463 --> 48:22.167
* I COULD HATE YOU,
I DON'T THINK I WILL *

48:22.200 --> 48:25.603
* IF YOU EVER
SEE ME ANYWHERE *

48:25.636 --> 48:28.339
* AND YOU KNOW ME,
PLEASE WALK AWAY... *

48:28.373 --> 48:29.975
WHY ISN'T THIS WORKING?

48:30.008 --> 48:33.111
ANGUS!
MOM?

48:33.144 --> 48:36.014
I'M WORKING
ON MY SCIENCE PROJECT.

48:36.047 --> 48:38.984
OH, OK!
YOU'RE NOT
WEARING THIS TIE.

48:39.017 --> 48:40.518
Grandpa: WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

48:40.551 --> 48:43.521
THAT'S A BEAUTIFUL
TIE.
IT'S A CLIP-ON!

48:43.554 --> 48:46.524
MEG, YOU'RE MAKING
EVERYBODY CRAZY.

48:46.557 --> 48:48.359
YOU'RE ON ME ALL THE TIME
ABOUT THE WEDDING.

48:48.393 --> 48:51.196
YOU'RE ALL OVER ANGUS ABOUT
THIS SCIENCE SCHOOL CRAP!

48:51.229 --> 48:53.364
IT'S NOT CRAP, DAD.
IT'S CRAP!

48:53.398 --> 48:55.366
IT'S A WONDERFUL
OPPORTUNITY FOR HIM.

48:55.400 --> 48:58.736
IT'S A CHANCE TO EXCEL
AT SOMETHING HE'S
REALLY GREAT AT!

48:58.769 --> 49:01.039
IT'S GOOD FOR ANGUS.

49:01.072 --> 49:02.673
IT'S ALSO
AN OPPORTUNITY FOR
HIM TO GO SOMEPLACE

49:02.707 --> 49:05.010
WHERE HE DOESN'T
HAVE TO ACCOUNT FOR
WHO HIS PARENTS ARE.

49:05.043 --> 49:06.377
SCREW WHAT
OTHER PEOPLE THINK.

49:06.411 --> 49:08.413
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO PROVE ANYTHING.

49:08.446 --> 49:10.181
NEITHER DOES HE.

49:10.215 --> 49:12.050
THIS DANCE THING
IS A PRANK.

49:12.083 --> 49:15.053
I DON'T WANT HIM
HUMILIATED IN FRONT
OF THE WHOLE SCHOOL.

49:15.086 --> 49:16.687
YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING?

49:16.721 --> 49:19.490
YOU'RE NOT GIVING THE BOY
CREDIT FOR BEING STRONG.

49:19.524 --> 49:21.692
YOU KNOW, EVERY
TIME HE SITS DOWN
IN THE CAFETERIA,

49:21.726 --> 49:23.228
THE KIDS JUMP UP
AND PRETEND

49:23.261 --> 49:24.295
THEY'RE BEING
THROWN OFF THE BENCH.

49:24.329 --> 49:26.397
THEY CALL HIM
"BIGFOOT."

49:26.431 --> 49:28.399
HE NEVER MENTIONED
THAT TO ME.

49:28.433 --> 49:30.235
HE NEVER TOLD ME EITHER.

49:30.268 --> 49:32.570
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY DID
WITH HIS UNDERWEAR?

49:32.603 --> 49:36.241
THEY RAN IT UP
THE FLAGPOLE
JUST TO HUMILIATE HIM.

49:36.274 --> 49:39.577
AND HE GETS UP,
AND HE GOES BACK THERE
EVERY SINGLE DAY.

49:39.610 --> 49:42.580
SO DON'T YOU TELL ME
I DON'T KNOW HOW
STRONG MY SON IS.

49:42.613 --> 49:44.115
I KNOW.

49:44.149 --> 49:45.783
AND IF HE WANTS TO GO
TO ANY GOD DAMN SCHOOL

49:45.816 --> 49:47.785
WHERE THE KIDS WON'T
SLAP THEIR BELLIES

49:47.818 --> 49:50.488
EVERY TIME HE WALKS BY,
THEN HE DAMN WELL CAN!

49:51.756 --> 49:55.426
THAT WAS YOU, KID.

49:55.460 --> 49:57.428
THIRD GRADE.

49:57.462 --> 49:59.697
LOOK HOW YOU TURNED OUT.

49:59.730 --> 50:01.632
[CHUCKLES]

50:08.739 --> 50:12.277
Singer: * DOIN' EVERYTHING
I WANNA DO *

50:12.310 --> 50:15.613
* MAYBE SOMEDAY
YOU WOULD BE THERE *

50:15.646 --> 50:19.584
* I THOUGHT WE WOULD
ALWAYS GET ALONG *

50:19.617 --> 50:23.221
* I LIKE EVERYONE,
THEY ALL HATE ME *

50:23.254 --> 50:26.691
* FUNNY FACE, WHAT'S
WRONG WITH YOU ANYWAY? *

50:26.724 --> 50:30.395
* FUNNY FACE,
WHY DO I CARE *

50:30.428 --> 50:37.568
* OHH OHH OHH OHH

50:37.602 --> 50:45.643
* OHHH OHHH OHH OHH

50:45.676 --> 50:48.613
[STIFLED LAUGHING]

50:48.646 --> 50:51.449
IS THIS--
IS THIS A BAD TIME?

50:51.482 --> 50:55.520
[POP, AIR ESCAPING]

50:55.553 --> 50:58.323
[LAUGHS]

50:58.356 --> 51:00.258
IS THIS A FRIEND?

51:00.291 --> 51:05.496
MOM.
I JUST WANTED TO SAY HI.

51:06.897 --> 51:08.366
HI.

51:08.399 --> 51:10.501
LOOK, ANGUS,
YOUR INTERVIEW
IS ON THE 22nd.

51:10.535 --> 51:12.103
YOU KNOW HOW
SOON THAT IS?

51:12.137 --> 51:15.340
I KNOW WHEN THE 22nd IS,
MOM. TRUST ME.

51:15.373 --> 51:17.508
IT'S THE DAY
OF THE DANCE.
ALL RIGHT.

51:17.542 --> 51:19.177
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN--

51:19.210 --> 51:21.479
MOM--I...

51:24.515 --> 51:25.483
FORGET IT.

51:25.516 --> 51:28.519
THE INTERVIEW IS
AT 3:00.

51:28.553 --> 51:33.191
YOU'VE GOT PLENTY
OF TIME TO GET READY
FOR THE DANCE.

51:33.224 --> 51:34.492
MOM.

51:43.801 --> 51:45.770
HAAGEN-DAZS.

51:47.305 --> 51:49.207
[LAUGHING]

51:49.240 --> 51:50.875
WHY DON'T YOU BRING
YOUR LITTLE FRIEND?

52:14.799 --> 52:16.867
Angus, voice-over:
SINCE I COULD REMEMBER,

52:16.901 --> 52:19.404
MY GRANDFATHER WAS ALWAYS
THE BIG KID DOWN THE HALL.

52:19.437 --> 52:21.239
[HORN HONKING]

52:21.272 --> 52:22.573
IT'S FUNNY HOW YOU CAN BE
SO COMFORTABLE WITH SOMEONE...

52:22.607 --> 52:24.575
THAT YOU THINK
THEY'LL ALWAYS BE THERE.

52:24.609 --> 52:27.578
AND THEN ONE DAY
YOU REALIZE THEY'RE NOT.

52:27.612 --> 52:30.315
Meg: THOSE ARE
THE SHRIMP ROLLS?

52:30.348 --> 52:32.583
I THOUGHT
THEY'D BE BIGGER.

52:32.617 --> 52:35.386
OH, GOD. ARE THOSE
THE MEATBALLS?

52:35.420 --> 52:37.488
SHH.
I DIDN'T
ORDER ENOUGH FOOD.

52:37.522 --> 52:40.458
Man: MEG, THERE
IS ENOUGH FOOD HERE
TO FEED TWO ARMIES.

52:41.926 --> 52:44.262
ANGUS?

52:44.295 --> 52:46.297
ANGUS?

52:46.331 --> 52:48.499
ANGUS, UM, COULD YOU
HELP ME FOR A SECOND?

52:55.806 --> 52:58.743
UM, I WANT YOU
TO TELL ME THE TRUTH.

52:58.776 --> 53:01.846
THE ROSETTE--
WITH OR WITHOUT?

53:02.947 --> 53:05.250
E-EITHER WAY.

53:05.283 --> 53:08.286
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I'M SO NERVOUS.

53:08.319 --> 53:10.621
I SENT A SCHEDULE
FOR GRANDPA'S PILLS.

53:10.655 --> 53:13.458
OH, I KNOW IT.
12:00 AND 5:00.

53:13.491 --> 53:15.893
1:00 AND 4:00.

53:15.926 --> 53:19.630
OH. I'VE GOT IT
ALL WRITTEN DOWN
IN THIS BOOK.

53:19.664 --> 53:22.700
ANGUS, I PROMISE
I WON'T FORGET.
REALLY, I PROMISE.

53:24.669 --> 53:27.972
WOULD YOU PLEASE TELL
MY HUSBAND-TO-BE...

53:28.005 --> 53:30.608
THAT HIS FUTURE WIFE
IS ALMOST READY?

53:40.818 --> 53:43.454
GRANDPA?

53:43.488 --> 53:45.256
APRIL SAID
SHE'S ALMOST READY.

53:45.290 --> 53:46.424
GOOD, GOOD.

53:46.457 --> 53:47.625
[CHUCKLES]

53:47.658 --> 53:50.995
I TELL YOU, I--
I FEEL LIKE A KID.

53:51.028 --> 53:54.699
HA HA! LOOK AT ME.
I'M NERVOUS.

53:54.732 --> 53:56.834
LOOK,
I-I'M SWEATING.

53:56.867 --> 53:58.336
I GOT A LITTLE SECRET
FOR YOU.

53:58.369 --> 53:59.504
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

53:59.537 --> 54:01.272
I FEEL LIKE IT'S
MY WEDDING DAY.

54:01.306 --> 54:02.673
THIS IS YOUR WEDDING
DAY, GRANDPA.

54:02.707 --> 54:04.409
HOW DOES APRIL LOOK?

54:04.442 --> 54:06.344
SHE WOULDN'T LET ME
SEE HER WEDDING DRESS.

54:06.377 --> 54:09.013
I TELL YOU, THAT WOMAN.

54:09.046 --> 54:10.848
EVERY TIME
I LOOK AT HER,

54:10.881 --> 54:12.850
I GET THE WORST PAIN...

54:12.883 --> 54:15.986
RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF MY STOMACH, YOU KNOW?

54:16.020 --> 54:17.922
IT'S A GREAT FEELING.

54:17.955 --> 54:19.857
I KNOW.

54:19.890 --> 54:22.026
THESE THINGS
ARE SO STUPID.

54:22.059 --> 54:24.995
YOUR MOTHER WOULDN'T
LET ME WEAR A CLIP-ON.

54:25.029 --> 54:27.398
NOBODY CAN TELL.

54:30.100 --> 54:32.002
I'M SORRY
ABOUT THE OTHER DAY.

54:32.036 --> 54:33.704
AH, I FORGOT ABOUT IT.

54:33.738 --> 54:35.340
I REALLY FEEL BAD.

54:35.373 --> 54:36.541
IT'S FORGOTTEN.

54:36.574 --> 54:38.376
I DIDN'T MEAN
WHAT I SAID.

54:38.409 --> 54:39.977
I'M TELLING YOU,

54:40.010 --> 54:41.879
I DON'T EVEN
REMEMBER IT. I CAN'T
REMEMBER ANYTHING!

54:41.912 --> 54:43.681
NOT A GOD DAMN
THING ANYMORE. HUH.

54:54.058 --> 54:55.960
GRANDPA, I WAS A JERK.

54:58.763 --> 54:59.797
AND...

55:01.766 --> 55:05.035
I'M GLAD YOU'RE
MARRYING APRIL.

55:05.069 --> 55:06.804
YOU SHOULD SEE HER.

55:08.539 --> 55:10.475
I THINK SHE REALLY
LOVES YOU A LOT.

55:10.508 --> 55:11.909
BUT STILL...

55:11.942 --> 55:15.045
IT TAKES A LOT OF GUTS.

55:15.079 --> 55:17.348
YOU GOT BALLS, GRANDPA.

55:17.382 --> 55:19.417
MORE THAN ME.

55:19.450 --> 55:25.089
ANGUS, SUPERMAN
ISN'T BRAVE.

55:25.122 --> 55:27.458
DID YOU TAKE YOUR
PILL THIS MORNING?

55:27.492 --> 55:31.028
HA HA.
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

55:31.061 --> 55:34.532
HE'S SMART, HANDSOME,

55:34.565 --> 55:38.436
EVEN DECENT,
BUT HE'S NOT BRAVE.

55:38.469 --> 55:41.839
NOW, LISTEN TO ME.

55:41.872 --> 55:45.676
SUPERMAN IS INDESTRUCTIBLE.

55:45.710 --> 55:49.847
AND YOU CAN'T BE BRAVE...

55:49.880 --> 55:52.049
IF YOU'RE INDESTRUCTIBLE.

55:52.082 --> 55:54.952
IT'S PEOPLE LIKE YOU
AND YOUR MOTHER,

55:54.985 --> 55:59.424
PEOPLE WHO ARE...
DIFFERENT...

55:59.457 --> 56:02.827
AND CAN BE CRUSHED,
AND KNOW IT.

56:04.662 --> 56:07.097
YET THEY KEEP GOIN' ON
OUT THERE EVERY TIME.

56:10.134 --> 56:12.670
I'M NOT BRAVE, GRANDPA.

56:20.110 --> 56:23.814
I'M SO AFRAID OF
GOING TO THIS DANCE.

56:23.848 --> 56:27.652
AND I KNOW EVERYBODY
THINKS I'M STUPID
FOR TRYING,

56:27.685 --> 56:29.487
EVERYBODY BUT YOU.

56:35.693 --> 56:37.828
I WISH I COULD
JUST STOP LIKING
MELISSA,

56:37.862 --> 56:39.464
BUT I CAN'T.

56:41.165 --> 56:43.133
BECAUSE...

56:43.167 --> 56:46.103
NOW IT'S SORT OF
LIKE I HAVE A CHANCE,

56:46.136 --> 56:49.740
YOU KNOW,
TO BE WITH HER, I MEAN.

56:51.175 --> 56:52.643
I'M NOT CRAZY.

56:54.178 --> 56:56.681
I KNOW SHE'S NOT GONNA
BE STRUCK BLIND...

56:56.714 --> 56:58.148
AND ASK ME TO TAKE
HER HOME FROM THE DANCE

56:58.182 --> 57:00.685
OR ANYTHING.

57:00.718 --> 57:03.588
BUT IT'S THE ONLY
CHANCE I'LL HAVE.

57:06.056 --> 57:09.159
AND I GUESS...

57:09.193 --> 57:12.597
I JUST WANT
ONE MOMENT WITH HER.

57:12.630 --> 57:13.998
JUST ONE.

57:16.066 --> 57:18.002
I JUST WANT MY MOMENT.

57:49.099 --> 57:51.636
[NEEDLE DROPS ON RECORD]

57:51.669 --> 57:53.571
[TRUMPET PLAYING "REVEILLE"]

58:02.613 --> 58:04.048
GRANDPA?

58:10.955 --> 58:12.757
I'M SO GLAD YOU
WERE ABLE TO DO THIS.

58:12.790 --> 58:13.891
IT'S A PLEASURE.

58:13.924 --> 58:15.092
IT MEANS SO MUCH TO DADDY.

58:15.125 --> 58:17.662
IN THE MORNING,
I MIGHT NOT BE HERE.

58:17.695 --> 58:20.164
[LAUGHING]

58:22.166 --> 58:24.001
[SOBBING]

58:34.311 --> 58:37.948
[SONG PLAYING ON SOUNDTRACK]

58:37.982 --> 58:41.886
* WILL THE RIVER
CARRY ME ON *

58:41.919 --> 58:45.756
* LIVIN' RIVER
CARRY ME ON *

58:45.790 --> 58:49.627
* RIVER, RIVER
CARRY ME ON *

58:49.660 --> 58:53.330
* TO THE PLACE
WHERE I COME FROM *

58:53.363 --> 58:59.069
* SO DEEP, SO WIDE

59:00.671 --> 59:04.809
* WILL YOU TAKE ME
ON YOUR BACK *

59:04.842 --> 59:06.844
* FOR A RIDE

59:09.313 --> 59:13.784
* IF I SHOULD FALL

59:15.920 --> 59:19.023
* WOULD YOU SWALLOW ME

59:19.056 --> 59:22.092
* DEEP INSIDE

59:24.862 --> 59:29.867
* RIVER, SHOW ME
HOW TO FLOAT *

59:32.637 --> 59:37.942
* I FEEL LIKE
I'M SINKING DOWN *

59:40.344 --> 59:45.249
* THOUGHT THAT I COULD

59:45.282 --> 59:48.218
* GET ALONG

59:48.252 --> 59:52.189
* BUT HERE IN THIS WATER

59:52.222 --> 59:55.259
* MY FEET
WON'T TOUCH THE GROUND *

59:58.228 --> 01:00:05.636
* GOING AWAY

01:00:05.670 --> 01:00:07.705
* AWAY

01:00:07.738 --> 01:00:12.609
* TOWARD THE SEA

01:00:14.078 --> 01:00:18.883
* RIVER DEEP

01:00:20.751 --> 01:00:26.190
* CAN YOU LIFT UP
AND CARRY ME *

01:00:28.759 --> 01:00:29.927
WHAT HAPPENED?

01:00:33.097 --> 01:00:34.932
FELL OFF MY BIKE.

01:00:34.965 --> 01:00:37.334
PRETTY STUPID, HUH?

01:00:37.367 --> 01:00:39.336
IT'S A BABE MAGNET.

01:00:41.338 --> 01:00:44.341
SO WHEN YOU COMING
BACK TO SCHOOL?

01:00:44.374 --> 01:00:46.043
TOMORROW.

01:00:50.748 --> 01:00:53.918
I GUESS YOU'RE NOT
GOING TO THE DANCE.

01:00:53.951 --> 01:00:57.054
I'M NOT GOING
TO THE DANCE, OK?

01:00:57.087 --> 01:00:58.923
OK.

01:01:00.791 --> 01:01:03.761
MY INTERVIEW
FOR JEFFERSON'S
ON SATURDAY.

01:01:03.794 --> 01:01:07.364
THAT'S GREAT, MAN.
WHO NEEDS IT, RIGHT?

01:01:07.397 --> 01:01:09.867
HEY, WE CAN RENT A VIDEO.

01:01:09.900 --> 01:01:12.002
I HEAR CINDY CRAWFORD'S GOT
A NEW BUTT AND THIGH WORKOUT--

01:01:12.036 --> 01:01:13.337
SHUT UP, TROY!

01:01:21.846 --> 01:01:24.314
YOU JUST DON'T KNOW
HOW IT FEELS!

01:01:27.985 --> 01:01:31.488
I DON'T KNOW HOW IT FEELS?

01:01:31.521 --> 01:01:33.290
YOU THINK YOU'RE
THE ONLY PERSON ON EARTH

01:01:33.323 --> 01:01:36.193
WHO WAKES UP
EVERY MORNING WISHING
THEY WERE SOMEONE ELSE?

01:01:36.226 --> 01:01:38.195
TROY, I WANTED
TO GO TO THE DANCE!

01:01:38.228 --> 01:01:39.797
DON'T YOU GET IT?

01:01:39.830 --> 01:01:41.999
THEN WHY AREN'T YOU GOING?

01:01:42.032 --> 01:01:43.901
BECAUSE...

01:01:43.934 --> 01:01:47.772
I THINK I HAVE
TO STOP WANTING
THINGS SO MUCH.

01:02:14.865 --> 01:02:16.266
CAN I HELP YOU?

01:02:22.506 --> 01:02:24.308
HI, ANGUS.

01:02:24.341 --> 01:02:25.475
HI.

01:02:30.881 --> 01:02:33.550
DO YOU WANNA
COME IN?

01:02:33.583 --> 01:02:34.919
UM...

01:02:38.055 --> 01:02:39.456
NO, I DON'T THINK SO.

01:02:39.489 --> 01:02:41.158
WE HAVE FOOD.

01:02:41.191 --> 01:02:44.361
[BEEPING]

01:02:44.394 --> 01:02:46.230
[BEEPING STOPS]

01:02:47.397 --> 01:02:49.266
IT'S TIME FOR IVAN'S PILL.

01:02:52.970 --> 01:02:56.073
SEE? I DID REMEMBER.

01:03:01.545 --> 01:03:04.381
THIS IS FOR YOU.

01:03:04.414 --> 01:03:07.918
IVAN LEFT IT FOR YOU
AT MY HOUSE.

01:03:22.432 --> 01:03:24.234
[SNIFFLES, LAUGHS]

01:03:24.268 --> 01:03:26.070
IT'S AN AWFUL COLOR,
ISN'T IT?

01:03:26.103 --> 01:03:27.938
IT'S PLUM.

01:03:45.122 --> 01:03:48.058
I LOOK LIKE
MOBY GRAPE.

01:03:49.293 --> 01:03:51.495
YOU LOOK TERRIFIC.

01:03:56.133 --> 01:03:59.269
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO GET HURT.

01:03:59.303 --> 01:04:01.638
I WON'T, MOM.

01:04:01.671 --> 01:04:03.473
AS LONG AS
YOU LET ME GO.

01:04:06.043 --> 01:04:08.512
I CAN DO THIS.

01:04:08.545 --> 01:04:10.080
I KNOW YOU CAN.

01:04:15.619 --> 01:04:18.155
I CAN'T DO THIS.

01:04:18.188 --> 01:04:21.558
YES, YOU CAN.
NO, I CAN'T.

01:04:21.591 --> 01:04:23.127
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

01:04:23.160 --> 01:04:26.230
MY INTERVIEWER
FROM JEFFERSON'S HERE.

01:04:29.166 --> 01:04:33.971
YES, YOUR INTERVIEWER
FROM JEFFERSON,
MR. KESSLER,

01:04:34.004 --> 01:04:35.973
IS HERE.

01:04:36.006 --> 01:04:37.474
I WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE HERE AT 3:00,

01:04:37.507 --> 01:04:39.276
BUT TRAFFIC WAS
BUMPER-TO-BUMPER...

01:04:39.309 --> 01:04:42.479
WITH EVERY DROOLING,
MOUTH-BREATHING
BOTTOM-FEEDER...

01:04:42.512 --> 01:04:46.250
FROM HERE TO
MINNEAPOLIS GOING TO
THE FOOTBALL GAME.

01:04:46.283 --> 01:04:49.553
MINDLESS SPORT.

01:04:49.586 --> 01:04:51.488
IT'S GOING
TO TAKE ME AT LEAST
A FEW HOURS...

01:04:51.521 --> 01:04:55.492
TO ASSESS YOUR
QUALIFICATIONS AND
ANALYZE YOUR WORK.

01:04:55.525 --> 01:04:59.629
I ASSUME YOU'RE NOT
GOING ANYWHERE.

01:04:59.663 --> 01:05:02.466
W-WE ALWAYS
DRESS FOR DINNER.

01:05:09.039 --> 01:05:11.008
SO, YOU WANT TO
ATTEND JEFFERSON.

01:05:11.041 --> 01:05:12.376
THAT'S NOT DIFFICULT
TO UNDERSTAND;

01:05:12.409 --> 01:05:14.711
WE HAVE AN
EXCEPTIONAL PROGRAM.

01:05:14.744 --> 01:05:18.048
I WENT THERE MYSELF
WHEN I WAS YOUR AGE.

01:05:18.082 --> 01:05:21.018
IT WAS A REWARDING
EXPERIENCE WITH...

01:05:21.051 --> 01:05:22.519
OBVIOUS BENEFITS.

01:05:22.552 --> 01:05:26.023
NOW, IF I COULD SEE
YOUR SCIENCE EXPERIMENT,

01:05:26.056 --> 01:05:27.457
MR. BETHUNE.

01:05:27.491 --> 01:05:32.362
DO YOU HAVE
A SCIENCE EXPERIMENT,
MR. BETHUNE?

01:05:32.396 --> 01:05:36.200
YES. YES, I DO.

01:05:36.233 --> 01:05:39.203
Kessler: MAY I SEE IT?

01:05:39.236 --> 01:05:41.238
YOU'RE LOOKING AT IT.

01:05:41.271 --> 01:05:43.173
IS THIS A JOKE,
MR. BETHUNE?

01:05:43.207 --> 01:05:44.708
NO.

01:05:44.741 --> 01:05:48.145
I'M HOPING TO PROVE THAT
WITHIN EVERY NORMAL SYSTEM...

01:05:48.178 --> 01:05:51.248
THERE EXISTS AN ABERRATION,
SOMETHING DIFFERENT.

01:05:51.281 --> 01:05:53.483
THE CHAOS THEORY.

01:05:53.517 --> 01:05:55.185
THE BETHUNE THEORY.

01:05:55.219 --> 01:05:57.687
YOUR HYPOTHESIS?

01:05:57.721 --> 01:06:00.390
WHEN A SMALL, ABNORMAL
ELEMENT IS FORCED

01:06:00.424 --> 01:06:02.592
INTO A LARGER,
NORMAL SYSTEM,

01:06:02.626 --> 01:06:06.296
THE ELEMENT WILL EITHER
BE REJECTED OR DESTROYED.

01:06:06.330 --> 01:06:08.598
OBVIOUSLY.

01:06:08.632 --> 01:06:12.269
BUT IT DOESN'T HAVE
TO BE THAT WAY. IF--

01:06:12.302 --> 01:06:13.703
"IF"?

01:06:13.737 --> 01:06:17.341
IF THE ELEMENT IS BRAVE.

01:06:17.374 --> 01:06:19.543
Kessler: BRAVE?

01:06:19.576 --> 01:06:21.711
IF THE ELEMENT
CAN HOLD OUT LONG ENOUGH

01:06:21.745 --> 01:06:26.783
AND FACE THE TORMENT OF
THE SYSTEM UNTIL THE SYSTEM'S
ENERGY IS DEPLETED,

01:06:26.816 --> 01:06:29.019
IF THE ELEMENT CAN LOOK
THE SYSTEM IN THE EYE AND SAY,

01:06:29.053 --> 01:06:31.155
"I'M STILL HERE, ASSHOLE,"

01:06:31.188 --> 01:06:36.260
THEN THE SYSTEM WILL HAVE
TO CHANGE, ADAPT, MUTATE.

01:06:36.293 --> 01:06:39.096
AND IF THIS HAPPENS,
IT'LL HAVE PROVED
MY FRICKING POINT.

01:06:39.129 --> 01:06:42.232
WHICH IS...WHAT?

01:06:47.471 --> 01:06:49.439
THERE IS NO "NORMAL."

01:06:52.709 --> 01:06:54.144
ANGUS,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

01:06:56.313 --> 01:06:57.681
TO MUTATE.

01:07:02.619 --> 01:07:03.787
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:07:03.820 --> 01:07:05.655
[EXCITED CHATTER]

01:07:09.326 --> 01:07:10.660
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

01:07:10.694 --> 01:07:13.563
I'M THE ENTERTAINMENT.

01:07:18.802 --> 01:07:23.173
ANGUS, RICK'S GONNA
DO SOMETHING TO YOU.
I KNOW.

01:07:23.207 --> 01:07:25.475
SCREW HIM.
I WANT MY MOMENT.

01:07:25.509 --> 01:07:28.778
AND IF YOU CAN'T
STAND TO WATCH, THEN
DON'T! TAKE OFF!

01:07:28.812 --> 01:07:31.381
TELL YOUR MOM.
GET A LIFE.

01:07:31.415 --> 01:07:33.150
SCREW YOU!

01:07:33.183 --> 01:07:34.818
SCREW YOU!

01:07:37.521 --> 01:07:39.656
WANNA WALK IN
TOGETHER?
YEAH.

01:07:39.689 --> 01:07:41.658
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

01:07:54.704 --> 01:07:56.340
* ...ENOUGH IS ENOUGH

01:07:56.373 --> 01:07:59.343
* I HAVE NO ONE ELSE
TO BLAME.... *

01:07:59.376 --> 01:08:00.810
ANGUS?

01:08:00.844 --> 01:08:02.512
WHAT?

01:08:02.546 --> 01:08:04.448
I GOT TO GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

01:08:04.481 --> 01:08:05.449
WHATEVER.

01:08:05.482 --> 01:08:07.417
* ENOUGH TO ENOUGH

01:08:07.451 --> 01:08:09.786
* I HAVE NO ONE ELSE
TO BLAME, I JUST
WANT IT TO BE THE SAME *

01:08:09.819 --> 01:08:13.290
* SHUT UP
AND WE'LL BE FINE *

01:08:30.506 --> 01:08:32.475
NICE TUX.

01:08:32.509 --> 01:08:34.711
IT'S PURPLE.

01:08:34.743 --> 01:08:36.380
IT'S PLUM.

01:08:36.412 --> 01:08:39.448
YOU LOOK
LIKE BARNEY.

01:08:39.483 --> 01:08:40.850
OH, HEY, HOW ABOUT
AN HORS D'OEUVRE?

01:08:40.884 --> 01:08:42.386
LET'S DO PUNCH.

01:08:42.419 --> 01:08:43.819
OK. COME ON.

01:08:43.853 --> 01:08:45.189
[NEW SONG PLAYING]

01:08:45.221 --> 01:08:47.724
WELL, LOOKS LIKE
I'LL BE HANDING

01:08:47.756 --> 01:08:50.294
THIS LOVELY THING
OVER TO YOU FOR AWHILE.

01:08:53.763 --> 01:08:55.865
GIVE HER A CHANCE
TO MAKE A COMPARISON.

01:08:55.899 --> 01:09:00.437
YOU KNOW, LET HER DECIDE
WHAT'S MORE IMPORTANT:
QUALITY OR QUANTITY.

01:09:00.470 --> 01:09:02.171
RICK.

01:09:02.206 --> 01:09:04.573
[PRINCIPAL OVER P.A.]
CAN I HAVE YOUR
ATTENTION, PLEASE?

01:09:04.608 --> 01:09:07.844
WILL THE WINTER BALL
KING AND QUEEN PLEASE
COME BEHIND THE STAGE

01:09:07.877 --> 01:09:09.879
TO ARRANGE
FOR YOUR ENTRANCE?

01:09:09.912 --> 01:09:13.917
WELL, I GUESS YOU TWO
GUYS ARE ON, HUH?
YOU'RE IN GOOD HANDS.

01:09:15.785 --> 01:09:19.423
GOOD LUCK, ANGUS.

01:09:19.456 --> 01:09:22.326
Singer:
* WELL, I KNOW I'D BE A FOOL

01:09:22.359 --> 01:09:24.394
* TO GO BACK TO YOU

01:09:29.499 --> 01:09:34.438
* AND MANY TIMES,
I'VE TRIED TO RUN AWAY *

01:09:34.470 --> 01:09:37.774
* TOO VULNERABLE
TO EVERY WORD YOU'VE SAID *

01:09:37.807 --> 01:09:40.444
* IS IT SO HARD TO BELIEVE

01:09:40.477 --> 01:09:42.679
* WHAT YOU DO TO ME

01:09:42.712 --> 01:09:43.846
[SPITS]

01:09:47.817 --> 01:09:49.618
AW, MAN.
YOU'RE NASTY, MAN.

01:09:49.653 --> 01:09:50.886
IT'S PUNCH.

01:09:50.920 --> 01:09:52.788
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

01:09:59.329 --> 01:10:01.498
HERE ARE YOUR
OFFICIAL CROWNS.

01:10:04.501 --> 01:10:08.938
NOW, WHEN THE DEEJAY
FINISHES THIS SONG,
I'LL SAY A FEW WORDS.

01:10:08.972 --> 01:10:11.908
THEN YOU'LL HAVE
YOUR OFFICIAL WALK
DOWN THE STEPS.

01:10:11.941 --> 01:10:15.679
THEY'LL PLAY YOUR SONG,
AND THAT'S WHEN YOU'LL
HAVE YOUR DANCE.

01:10:15.712 --> 01:10:20.784
ANGUS, WHY DON'T YOU
PIN THAT ON MELISSA NOW?

01:10:30.827 --> 01:10:33.863
Principal: SETTLE DOWN,
PEOPLE. PLEASE SETTLE DOWN NOW.

01:10:33.897 --> 01:10:35.965
THANK YOU...

01:10:35.999 --> 01:10:40.370
I SWEAT WHENEVER
I GET NERVOUS. DON'T YOU?

01:10:40.404 --> 01:10:41.738
YEAH, WELL, YOU KNOW.

01:10:41.771 --> 01:10:43.940
YEAH, WELL,

01:10:43.973 --> 01:10:45.842
I GUESS IT'S EASIER 'CAUSE
GUYS ARE SUPPOSED TO SWEAT.

01:10:45.875 --> 01:10:47.577
OH, WELL, YOU KNOW.

01:10:47.611 --> 01:10:50.847
Principal:
I HAVE A SMALL LECTURE
ON DANCE FLOOR SAFETY.

01:10:50.880 --> 01:10:51.881
[SCATTERED BOOS]

01:10:51.915 --> 01:10:53.750
Principal: NO, NO, REALLY!

01:10:53.783 --> 01:10:55.285
AFTER THAT PRESENTATION
THE OTHER DAY

01:10:55.319 --> 01:10:56.286
WITH THE SENIOR DRAMA CLASS,
I ACTUALLY SLIPPED--

01:10:56.320 --> 01:10:57.454
IT'S JUST--

01:10:57.487 --> 01:11:00.824
EVERYONE WILL BE
STARING AT US.

01:11:00.857 --> 01:11:02.659
Principal: ...OUT THERE.
NOT GOOD.

01:11:04.894 --> 01:11:07.631
BUT YOU MUST
BE USED TO PEOPLE
STARING AT YOU.

01:11:07.664 --> 01:11:13.903
THE BIG MOMENT--
HERE IS THIS YEAR'S
WINTER BALL...

01:11:13.937 --> 01:11:15.372
KING AND QUEEN!

01:11:15.405 --> 01:11:17.674
LET'S HEAR IT!
HERE THEY ARE!

01:11:17.707 --> 01:11:19.543
[CROWD CHEERING]

01:11:28.585 --> 01:11:31.555
Principal: YOUR CROWNS.
DON'T FORGET YOUR CROWNS.

01:11:33.957 --> 01:11:37.627
Boy:
AH, HELL. NICE TUX.

01:11:37.661 --> 01:11:39.696
PLEASE DON'T TRIP.

01:11:39.729 --> 01:11:41.698
DON'T TRIP, MELISSA.
DON'T TRIP, MELISSA.

01:11:48.772 --> 01:11:50.707
DON'T TRIP, MELISSA.

01:11:55.845 --> 01:11:57.747
[ANGUS ON VIDEOTAPE]
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:11:57.781 --> 01:11:59.416
[TROY ON VIDEOTAPE]
TAPING THIS.

01:11:59.449 --> 01:12:00.784
[ANGUS ON VIDEOTAPE]
GET OUT OF HERE.

01:12:00.817 --> 01:12:02.752
ANGUS,
IT'S WHAT JOCKS DO...

01:12:02.786 --> 01:12:05.054
SO THEY CAN SEE WHERE
THEY'RE MAKING MISTAKES.

01:12:05.088 --> 01:12:08.425
NO ONE SEES THE
TAPE, AND YOU DON'T
TELL YOUR MOTHER?

01:12:08.458 --> 01:12:09.559
I DON'T
TELL HER EVERYTHING.

01:12:09.593 --> 01:12:10.860
LOOK UNDER HER
SHIRT.

01:12:10.894 --> 01:12:14.030
SHE'S ANATOMICALLY
CORRECT.

01:12:14.063 --> 01:12:17.066
HEY, A GIRL'S BOD
IS A GIRL'S BOD.

01:12:17.100 --> 01:12:18.835
Principal: YOU THERE...

01:12:18.868 --> 01:12:21.605
THERE'S MORE
TO GIRLS THAN JUST
THEIR BODS, GEEK.

01:12:21.638 --> 01:12:23.072
[TROY ON VIDEOTAPE]
RIGHT. AND YOU GO
NUTS FOR MELISSA

01:12:23.106 --> 01:12:25.375
BECAUSE OF HER GRADES?

01:12:25.409 --> 01:12:27.010
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL, OK?
THERE'S SOMETHING ABOUT HER.

01:12:27.043 --> 01:12:28.445
IT'S HER BOD, BUD.

01:12:28.478 --> 01:12:30.414
Principal: TURN IT OFF!

01:12:30.447 --> 01:12:33.082
NO, TROY,
I DON'T KNOW WHAT IT IS.

01:12:33.116 --> 01:12:34.784
Principal:
TURN IT OFF! TURN THAT OFF.

01:12:34.818 --> 01:12:36.486
I GET THE WORST PAIN IN MY
STOMACH WHENEVER I SEE HER.

01:12:36.520 --> 01:12:39.088
YOU GET A BONER
IN YOUR STOMACH?

01:12:39.122 --> 01:12:42.058
Girl: ALL RIGHT, ANGUS!

01:12:42.091 --> 01:12:43.760
ANGUS!

01:12:43.793 --> 01:12:44.994
[LAUGHTER, APPLAUSE]

01:12:45.028 --> 01:12:46.530
MELISSA.

01:12:46.563 --> 01:12:48.798
ALL RIGHT,
ANGUS!

01:12:48.832 --> 01:12:50.066
WHOO!

01:12:50.099 --> 01:12:52.802
[APPLAUSE]

01:12:52.836 --> 01:12:54.370
WHOO!

01:12:58.141 --> 01:12:59.909
ARE YOU GOING
SOMEWHERE, RICK?

01:12:59.943 --> 01:13:02.011
UH, YEAH. I NEED TO GET
SOME FRESH AIR.

01:13:02.045 --> 01:13:05.114
OH, YOU KNOW THE RULES.
NO IN-OUT PRIVILEGES
AT SCHOOL DANCES.

01:13:05.148 --> 01:13:06.650
WHAT ABOUT THEM?

01:13:06.683 --> 01:13:08.652
THEY'RE
THE KING AND QUEEN.

01:13:08.685 --> 01:13:11.488
I'M MAKING AN EXCEPTION
FOR THEM.

01:13:11.521 --> 01:13:13.156
[GIRL SNIFFLING]

01:13:27.537 --> 01:13:28.672
MELISSA...

01:13:31.708 --> 01:13:33.477
I WAS AN IDIOT.

01:13:35.044 --> 01:13:36.646
I'M SORRY.

01:13:39.148 --> 01:13:40.750
WHAT A JERK!

01:13:45.188 --> 01:13:48.692
I'M REALLY SORRY.

01:13:48.725 --> 01:13:51.995
NOT YOU, HIM.

01:13:55.164 --> 01:13:57.066
DO YOU...

01:13:57.100 --> 01:14:00.036
EVER GET TIRED
OF WHO YOU ARE?

01:14:01.571 --> 01:14:03.640
DO YOU KNOW WHO
YOU'RE TALKING TO?

01:14:10.079 --> 01:14:12.949
DO YOU WANT TO KNOW
SOMETHING ABOUT ME?

01:14:12.982 --> 01:14:15.218
I'D LIKE TO KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT YOU.

01:14:17.921 --> 01:14:19.556
I'M BULIMIC.

01:14:23.159 --> 01:14:25.194
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT IS?

01:14:25.228 --> 01:14:27.597
I'M A FAT KID.

01:14:27.631 --> 01:14:29.899
YEAH, I KNOW
WHAT THAT IS.

01:14:29.933 --> 01:14:31.735
IT'S WHEN YOU
EAT TOO MUCH

01:14:31.768 --> 01:14:34.170
AND CHUCK IT UP
SO YOU DON'T TURN
OUT TO LOOK LIKE ME.

01:14:35.772 --> 01:14:36.940
CLOSE ENOUGH.

01:14:36.973 --> 01:14:40.109
ACTUALLY, I EVEN
TRIED IT ONCE.

01:14:40.143 --> 01:14:42.946
BUT WHEN I STUCK
MY FINGER DOWN
MY THROAT,

01:14:42.979 --> 01:14:45.715
I WAS STILL
HUNGRY AND I
ALMOST ATE MY ARM.

01:14:45.749 --> 01:14:47.617
[LAUGHS]

01:14:49.052 --> 01:14:52.121
YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON
I'VE EVER TOLD.

01:14:52.155 --> 01:14:54.958
ANGUS...

01:14:54.991 --> 01:14:57.060
I THINK WE HAVE
TO GO BACK INSIDE.

01:14:57.093 --> 01:15:01.064
THEN I THINK
I HAVE TO TELL YOU,
I CAN'T DANCE.

01:15:02.632 --> 01:15:04.801
WE'LL SURVIVE.

01:15:04.834 --> 01:15:09.906
I DIDN'T SAY
"I CAN'T DANCE WELL."
I SAID, "I CAN'T DANCE."

01:15:09.939 --> 01:15:12.108
MY LIMBS
ARE LETHAL WEAPONS

01:15:12.141 --> 01:15:13.810
'CAUSE
PEOPLE HAVE BEEN
BADLY HURT

01:15:13.843 --> 01:15:15.511
TRYING
TO DANCE WITH ME.

01:15:27.123 --> 01:15:32.128
* EACH AND EVERY DAY

01:15:32.161 --> 01:15:37.133
* EACH AND EVERY

01:15:37.166 --> 01:15:39.168
* EACH AND EVERY...

01:15:39.202 --> 01:15:40.637
[SONG FADES]

01:15:40.670 --> 01:15:42.672
Principal: YOUR WINTER
BALL KING AND QUEEN

01:15:42.706 --> 01:15:45.274
WILL START
THEIR DANCE NOW.

01:15:45.308 --> 01:15:47.577
[NEW SONG PLAYING]

01:15:49.012 --> 01:15:53.783
Singer: * I WANNA HOLD
THE HAND INSIDE YOU *

01:15:58.021 --> 01:15:59.823
* I WANNA TAKE
A BREATH LIKE YOU *

01:15:59.856 --> 01:16:02.291
DON'T WORRY.
I PICKED A SLOW SONG.

01:16:02.325 --> 01:16:04.227
WE WON'T HAVE
TO MOVE MUCH.

01:16:07.030 --> 01:16:10.166
* I LOOK TO YOU
AND I SEE NOTHING *

01:16:10.199 --> 01:16:12.802
ANGUS, RELAX.

01:16:16.339 --> 01:16:21.110
* I LOOK TO YOU
TO SEE THE TRUTH *

01:16:25.348 --> 01:16:27.183
* YOU LIVE YOUR LIFE

01:16:27.216 --> 01:16:28.885
* YOU GROW IN SHADOWS...

01:16:28.918 --> 01:16:30.754
[GASPS]

01:16:30.787 --> 01:16:31.755
I'M SORRY.

01:16:31.788 --> 01:16:34.023
[CHUCKLES]

01:16:34.057 --> 01:16:37.026
WAIT. WAIT. WAIT.
STOP. TRY THIS.

01:16:37.060 --> 01:16:38.862
LIKE, OK.

01:16:38.895 --> 01:16:43.800
FORWARD, TOUCH, SIDE,
TOGETHER.

01:16:43.833 --> 01:16:47.003
BACK, TOUCH,

01:16:47.036 --> 01:16:49.005
SIDE, TOGETHER.

01:16:52.909 --> 01:16:56.713
* CLOSE YOUR EYES
WITH WHAT'S NOT THERE *

01:16:56.746 --> 01:16:58.682
DON'T CONCENTRATE,
ANGUS.

01:17:02.085 --> 01:17:07.290
* FADE INTO YOU

01:17:11.260 --> 01:17:16.700
* STRANGE YOU NEVER KNEW

01:17:20.303 --> 01:17:22.706
* FADE

01:17:22.739 --> 01:17:23.940
* INTO YOU

01:17:23.973 --> 01:17:26.142
Go for it, Angus.

01:17:29.412 --> 01:17:34.751
* I THINK IT'S STRANGE
YOU NEVER KNEW *

01:18:13.456 --> 01:18:15.291
[CHEERING]

01:18:19.162 --> 01:18:21.998
HEY. WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:18:22.031 --> 01:18:23.933
[NEW SONG PLAYING]

01:18:26.435 --> 01:18:27.837
MELISSA,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

01:18:27.871 --> 01:18:29.806
RICK!
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

01:18:29.839 --> 01:18:31.507
LOOK AT THIS GUY! COME
ON! JOKE'S OVER, MAN.

01:18:31.540 --> 01:18:33.309
RICK, LEAVE ME ALONE!
HEY!

01:18:33.342 --> 01:18:35.444
WHAT, YOU GONNA DEFEND HER?
GET A LIFE, BETHUNE!

01:18:35.478 --> 01:18:36.479
Melissa: RICK!
RICK, STOP IT!

01:18:36.512 --> 01:18:38.047
I KEEP SAVING HER
FOR YOU.

01:18:38.081 --> 01:18:40.850
STOP!
IT'S TIME I BROKE
YOUR NOSE, ANGUS.

01:18:40.884 --> 01:18:44.020
TAKE YOUR BEST SHOT, ASSHO--

01:18:44.053 --> 01:18:47.356
COME ON, MAN.
KEEP--

01:18:47.390 --> 01:18:48.792
WELCOME TO HIGH SCHOOL,
ANGUS.

01:18:48.825 --> 01:18:50.126
[GROANS]

01:18:54.397 --> 01:18:56.065
GOOD THING
YOU'RE LEAVING.

01:19:02.438 --> 01:19:05.341
I'M STILL HERE, ASSHOLE.

01:19:05.374 --> 01:19:08.544
I'LL ALWAYS BE HERE!

01:19:08.577 --> 01:19:12.015
YOU PUSH ME DOWN AND I'LL GET
RIGHT BACK UP AGAIN, AGAIN,

01:19:12.048 --> 01:19:14.483
AND AGAIN, AGAIN, AND AGAIN!

01:19:14.517 --> 01:19:20.857
I COULD BEAT YOU RIGHT HERE
RIGHT NOW, BUT I DON'T WANT
TO BE BETTER THAN YOU, RICK!

01:19:20.890 --> 01:19:22.158
I DON'T WANT TO BE
BETTER THAN ANYBODY!

01:19:22.191 --> 01:19:23.927
I WANNA BE WHO I AM:

01:19:23.960 --> 01:19:26.930
A FAT KID WHO'S
GOOD AT SCIENCE
AND FAIR AT FOOTBALL!

01:19:26.963 --> 01:19:31.234
THAT'S WHO I AM!
I CAN LIVE WITH IT.
WHY CAN'T YOU?

01:19:31.267 --> 01:19:33.970
BECAUSE IT'S NOT NORMAL!
YOU'RE NOT NORMAL!

01:19:34.003 --> 01:19:35.171
AND WHO IS? YOU?

01:19:35.204 --> 01:19:36.873
YOU BET YOUR ASS.

01:19:36.906 --> 01:19:40.209
AND SO WHAT, TO BE NORMAL,
WE ALL HAVE TO BE LIKE YOU?

01:19:40.243 --> 01:19:44.347
THERE ARE 400 PEOPLE
IN THIS ROOM THAT ARE
NOTHING LIKE YOU!

01:19:44.380 --> 01:19:48.517
SOME OF THEM ARE FAT;
SOME OF THEM ARE SKINNY;
SOME OF THEM ARE TALL;

01:19:48.551 --> 01:19:50.519
SOME OF THEM ARE SHORT.

01:19:50.553 --> 01:19:53.022
SOME OF THEM HAVE BRACES;
SOME OF THEM HAVE BIRTHMARKS

01:19:53.056 --> 01:19:55.524
OR SCARS OR FRIZZY HAIR...

01:19:55.558 --> 01:19:59.062
OR EARS THAT STICK OUT.

01:19:59.095 --> 01:20:02.231
BUT MOST OF THEM PROBABLY
WALK THROUGH THESE HALLS
EVERY DAY...

01:20:02.265 --> 01:20:07.070
NEVER TELLING ANYBODY
THE TRUTH ABOUT WHAT THEY
WANT OR NEED OR BELIEVE...

01:20:07.103 --> 01:20:10.439
BECAUSE PEOPLE LIKE YOU,
NORMAL PEOPLE LIKE YOU,

01:20:10.473 --> 01:20:12.876
HAVE THEM TERRIFIED
OF BEING WHO THEY ARE.

01:20:12.909 --> 01:20:17.446
I MEAN, IF YOU'RE NORMAL,
WHAT DOES THAT MAKE THEM?

01:20:18.948 --> 01:20:20.950
SO, WHICH IS IT, RICK?

01:20:22.085 --> 01:20:23.552
ARE YOU NORMAL...

01:20:23.586 --> 01:20:26.155
OR ARE YOU JUST
ONE OF US?

01:20:26.189 --> 01:20:29.392
WHATEVER I AM, IT'S
SOMETHING YOU'RE
NEVER GONNA BE.

01:20:32.128 --> 01:20:33.529
THANK GOD.

01:20:37.133 --> 01:20:39.235
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

01:20:57.220 --> 01:20:58.454
[NEW SONG PLAYS]

01:20:58.487 --> 01:21:01.524
* YOU GAVE YOUR LOVE
TO ME SOFTLY... *

01:21:01.557 --> 01:21:03.292
I WANNA DANCE
ONE MORE.

01:21:03.326 --> 01:21:04.961
OK, I'LL WAIT
OVER BY THE TABLE.

01:21:04.994 --> 01:21:07.530
NO! I WANNA
DANCE IT WITH YOU.

01:21:07.563 --> 01:21:10.233
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.
I CAN'T--

01:21:10.266 --> 01:21:14.137
SCREW 'EM, ANGUS.
JUST DANCE.

01:21:14.170 --> 01:21:16.472
* ON AND ON AND ON

01:21:16.505 --> 01:21:22.311
* YOU GAVE YOUR LOVE
TO ME SOFTLY *

01:21:22.345 --> 01:21:26.882
* WHEN I'M FEELIN'
BLUE AND LONELY *

01:21:28.351 --> 01:21:33.389
* ALL I HAVE TO DO
IS THINK OF YOU *

01:21:33.422 --> 01:21:37.493
* WE HAD JUST ONE NIGHT,
BUT IT LINGERS *

01:21:37.526 --> 01:21:39.162
* ON AND ON AND ON...

01:21:39.195 --> 01:21:41.164
YOU WANNA SPAZ
OUT WITH ME ON
THE DANCE FLOOR?

01:21:41.197 --> 01:21:43.532
AND WATCH
ALL THE DILDOS?

01:21:43.566 --> 01:21:45.901
TROY, WE ARE
THOSE DILDOS.

01:21:47.370 --> 01:21:49.372
OK!

01:21:49.405 --> 01:21:52.141
* "BABY, DON'T YOU CRY"

01:21:52.175 --> 01:21:53.342
* "PUT YOUR ARMS
AROUND ME NOW"... *

01:21:53.376 --> 01:21:58.181
BUDS!
OHH! OHH.

01:22:01.084 --> 01:22:05.021
UM--YOU BROKE
HIS NOSE, UM...

01:22:05.054 --> 01:22:08.424
WEDBERG.
TROY WEDBERG.

01:22:16.399 --> 01:22:20.003
* YOU GAVE YOUR LOVE
TO ME SOFTLY *

01:22:20.036 --> 01:22:21.670
ANGUS!

01:22:21.704 --> 01:22:23.339
WOULD YOU
WALK ME HOME?

01:22:27.076 --> 01:22:30.213
YOU MEAN TONIGHT,
AFTER THE DANCE?

01:22:30.246 --> 01:22:34.317
* ...STAY WITH ME TONIGHT

01:22:34.350 --> 01:22:40.956
* LA LA LA LA LA LA...

01:24:10.813 --> 01:24:12.348
Angus, voice-over:
THE DANCE ENDED.

01:24:12.381 --> 01:24:14.150
SCHOOL CLOSED
FOR THE HOLIDAY.

01:24:14.183 --> 01:24:17.320
RICK SANFORD GOT SUSPENDED
FOR HIS LITTLE PRANK.

01:24:17.353 --> 01:24:20.489
I GOT INTO JEFFERSON,
BUT I DIDN'T GO.

01:24:20.523 --> 01:24:22.125
I SAID, "SCREW 'EM."

01:24:34.770 --> 01:24:38.341
I FINALLY KNEW
WHAT IT FELT LIKE TO BE
ON TOP OF THE WORLD.

01:24:38.374 --> 01:24:40.509
I HAD HAD MY MOMENT.

01:24:40.543 --> 01:24:43.179
AND THEN I HEARD
MY GRANDFATHER'S VOICE
SAY TO ME:

01:24:43.212 --> 01:24:47.116
"NOW GO HAVE ANOTHER."
MAYBE I WILL.

01:24:47.150 --> 01:24:51.354
WHO KNOWS?
MAYBE MELISSA LEFEVRE
ACTUALLY LIKES ME.

01:24:51.387 --> 01:24:53.556
ALL I KNOW IS,

01:24:53.589 --> 01:24:55.758
I'M STILL HERE.

01:25:11.240 --> 01:25:12.875
["J.A.R." BY GREEN DAY
PLAYING]

01:25:27.590 --> 01:25:30.426
* MY FRIEND DROVE OFF
THE OTHER DAY *

01:25:30.459 --> 01:25:32.728
* NOW HE'S GONE
AND ALL THEY SAY *

01:25:32.761 --> 01:25:36.365
* IS YOU GOT TO LIVE
'CAUSE LIFE GOES ON *

01:25:38.334 --> 01:25:40.903
* AND NOW I SEE
I'M MORTAL, TOO *

01:25:40.936 --> 01:25:43.472
* I CAN'T LIVE
MY LIFE LIKE YOU *

01:25:43.506 --> 01:25:46.875
* GOT TO LIVE IT UP
WHILE LIFE GOES ON *

01:25:49.445 --> 01:25:52.548
* AND I THINK
IT'S ALL RIGHT *

01:25:52.581 --> 01:25:54.417
* THAT I DO WHAT I LIKE

01:25:54.450 --> 01:25:58.421
* 'CAUSE THAT'S THE WAY
I WANNA LIVE *

01:25:58.454 --> 01:26:00.756
* IT'S HOW I GIVE

01:26:00.789 --> 01:26:03.326
* AND I'M STILL GIVIN'

01:26:07.330 --> 01:26:09.898
* AND NOW I WONDER
'BOUT MY FRIEND *

01:26:09.932 --> 01:26:12.435
* IF HE GAVE
ALL HE COULD GIVE *

01:26:12.468 --> 01:26:15.771
* 'CAUSE HE LIVED HIS LIFE
LIKE I LIVE MINE *

01:26:17.840 --> 01:26:20.609
* IF YOU COULD SEE
INSIDE MY HEAD *

01:26:20.643 --> 01:26:22.911
* THEN YOU'D START
TO UNDERSTAND *

01:26:22.945 --> 01:26:26.449
* THE THINGS I VALUE
IN MY HEART *

01:26:28.851 --> 01:26:31.920
* AND I THINK
IT'S ALL RIGHT *

01:26:31.954 --> 01:26:33.689
* THAT I DO WHAT I LIKE

01:26:33.722 --> 01:26:37.460
* 'CAUSE THAT'S THE WAY
I WANNA LIVE *

01:26:37.493 --> 01:26:40.296
* IT'S HOW I GIVE

01:26:40.329 --> 01:26:42.731
* AND I'M STILL GIVIN'

01:26:51.974 --> 01:26:54.643
* YOU KNOW THAT

01:26:54.677 --> 01:26:57.380
* WELL, I KNOW THAT

01:26:57.413 --> 01:27:00.916
* YOU'RE WATCHING ME

01:27:23.872 --> 01:27:26.842
* WELL, I THINK
IT'S ALL RIGHT *

01:27:26.875 --> 01:27:28.677
* THAT I DO WHAT I LIKE

01:27:28.711 --> 01:27:32.515
* 'CAUSE THAT'S THE WAY
I WANNA LIVE *

01:27:32.548 --> 01:27:34.983
* IT'S HOW I GIVE

01:27:35.017 --> 01:27:37.520
* I'M STILL GIVIN'

01:27:46.362 --> 01:27:48.697
* GOT TO MAKE A PLAN,
GOT TO DO WHAT'S RIGHT *

01:27:48.731 --> 01:27:51.367
* CAN'T RUN AROUND IN CIRCLES
IF YOU WANNA BUILD A LIFE *

01:27:51.400 --> 01:27:53.869
* BUT I DON'T WANNA MAKE
A PLAN FOR A DAY FAR AWAY *

01:27:53.902 --> 01:27:56.305
* WHILE I'M YOUNG
AND WHILE I'M ABLE
ALL I WANNA DO IS-- *

01:27:56.339 --> 01:27:58.674
[MARCHING BAND PLAYING]

01:28:12.588 --> 01:28:14.423
Troy: ANGUS!

01:28:14.457 --> 01:28:17.025
Kessler:
MR. BETHUNE.

01:28:17.059 --> 01:28:18.927
Meg: ANGUS!

01:28:18.961 --> 01:28:22.064
MR. BETHUNE.

01:28:22.097 --> 01:28:24.867
Jody: ANGUS...BETHUNE?

01:28:24.900 --> 01:28:26.702
Angus and Troy: ALL RIGHT!

01:29:56.925 --> 01:29:59.495
Troy: ANGUS!

01:29:59.528 --> 01:30:01.564
ANGUS!

